etherlands [->span<-] Asia [->span<-] Asia Training Center [->span<-] Keji 6th Road #59 [->span<-] Hwa\u2011Ya Technology Park [->span<-] Kuei\u2011Shan Township, Taoyuan County [->span<-] 33383 Taoyuan [->span<-] Taiwan [->span<-] Contact us [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Committed to accountability and transparency [->p<-] ASML has a two-tier board structure with a board of management responsible for managing the company under the supervision of an independent supervisory board. ASML\u2019s shares are listed on Euronext Amsterdam and NASDAQ. [->p<-] Our executives set and achieve the company\u2019s strategic direction, objectives and policies, and manage general affairs. ASML's Board of Management has five members. The CEO is the sole president and serves as the chair. [->p<-] The Supervisory Board consists of nine experienced business and technology professionals from around the world. In addition to overseeing business activities, they keep a keen eye on risk management, company culture, corporate social responsibility and the company\u2019s relationship with shareholders, and safeguard our integrity in reporting and compliance. [->p<-] Shareholders play an important role in ASML\u2019s governance. Next to the Board of Management and the Supervisory Board, shareholders participate in our general meetings, held at least once a year. [->p<-] We encourage ethical behavior at ASML, inside and out. Read more about our code of conduct here. [->p<-] Learn about ASML\u2019s risk management framework and how risk influences our strategy. [->p<-] The external auditor conducts financial audits in accordance with legal requirements and regularly provides the Audit Committee with its findings. [->p<-] Browse ASML\u2019s corporate governance policies and archives. [->p<-] Take a tour of the highlights to find out more about our performance and achievements, or download the full report. [->p<-] At ASML, everyone\u2019s voice matters. We uphold our code of conduct by respecting each employee\u2019s right to raise concerns and report issues."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] Read about who we are, what guides us, and how we strive to make the world better for future generations [->div<-] Read all our annual reports, explore our financial results and highlights [->div<-] Learn about the Annual General Meeting of Shareholders at ASML, including when the meeting convenes and historical shareholder information."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] "]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Corporate governance"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] 2025 Annual Report [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] Governance structure [->h3<-] Board of Management [->h3<-] Supervisory Board [->h3<-] Shareholders [->h3<-] Vision and mission [->h3<-] Annual reports [->h3<-] Shareholder meetings"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] View Articles of Association [->h4<-] Our values and principles [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] Our goal is to build a relationship of trust with our stakeholders, which include employees, customers, suppliers, shareholders and society. [->h5<-] We aim to be as open and transparent as possible about our structure, financial reporting, internal controls and procedures, and decision-making process. We also look for ways to improve by monitoring developments in corporate governance practice."]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 42 [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Code of Conduct [->span<-] How we manage risk [->span<-] Auditors [->span<-] Governance downloads [->span<-] Download [->span<-] 2025 Annual Report [->span<-] Speak Up [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] ASML\u2019s Board of Management has six members. The CEO is the sole president and serves as chair. [->p<-] The Supervisory Board appoints the members of the Board of Management and notifies shareholders at the\u00a0 [->p<-] . Members are appointed for a term of up to four years and may be reappointed for consecutive terms. [->p<-] French national, 1973, member of the Board of Management since 2018 (term expires in 2028). Christophe joined ASML in 2008 and has held several management positions in marketing and product management. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Christophe holds a masters\u2019 degree in physics from the Institut Polytechnique de Grenoble. Before ASML, he worked at semiconductor equipment industry peers KLA Tencor and Applied Materials. [->p<-] Dutch national, 1965. Roger joined ASML and was appointed a member of the Board of Management in 2018 (term expires in 2030). \u00a0 [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Roger joined ASML from Deloitte Touche Tohmatsu Ltd, where he held several roles. He has a master's degree in economics and business administration (1988), a post-master's degree in auditing (1990) and a PhD in business and economics (1995) from the University of Maastricht. [->p<-] French national, 1961. Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric joined ASML in 2009 as Executive Vice President and COO and was appointed to the Board of Management in 2010 (term expires in 2028).\u00a0 [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric joined ASML from French industrial and transport group Alstom. He is a graduate of Ecole Polytechnique (1985) and Ecole Nationale Superieure des Mines in Paris (1988). [->p<-] American national, 1967, member of the Board of Management since 2023 (term expires in 2027). Wayne joined ASML in 2018 as Executive Vice President of Customer Support. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Before he joined ASML, Wayne served as Senior Vice President of Global Manufacturing Operations and as Vice President of Wafer Fabs at Micron Technology, Inc, the company where he began his career in 1987 as a production operator. He continued to move into operations roles of increasing leadership in engineering, planning and production. [->p<-] American and Irish national, 1967. Jim joined ASML in 2007 and was appointed a member of the Board of Management in 2024 (term expires in 2028). [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Jim joined ASML in 2007 through the acquisition of Brion, where he was general manager from 2008 until 2015. He subsequently served as the CEO of Cymer and then led the Applications business for five years. Jim holds a Master of Science in Management from the MIT Sloan School of Management (1994) and a Master of Science in Aeronautics and Astronautics from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (1994). [->p<-] Dutch national, 1976. Marco joined ASML in 1999 and was appointed a member of the Board of Management in 2026 (term expires in 2030).\u00a0 [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Marco joined ASML in 1999 and has over 25 years of experience in various technical and leadership roles, including Executive Vice President for the business area Applications from 2023 until 2026. Marco has served as Executive Vice President and Chief Technology Officer since 2025. He holds a Master of Science (with honors) in Mathematics from Delft University of Technology. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Various roles in the technology sector (1999\u20132005) [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] For more information on how the Board of Management operates and makes decisions, as well as how members are appointed, download the rules of procedure. [->p<-] Rules of Procedure Board of Management [->p<-] The Supervisory Board Remuneration Committee determines the compensation of the members of the Board of Management according to the Remuneration Policy adopted at the AGM on April 23, 2025. For more details, see the Board of Management Remuneration Policy and the Remuneration Report. [->p<-] ASML Remuneration Policy Board of Management [->p<-] 2025 Remuneration Report (US GAAP)"]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] \n [->div<-] Meet our Supervisory Board members, who oversee and advise ASML\u2019s Board of Management. [->div<-] Read all our annual reports, explore our financial results and highlights [->div<-] We maintain a long-term commitment to our shareholders and value their input during annual meetings"]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] Chief Business Officer (2022\u20132024) [->li<-] Executive Vice President EUV (2018\u20132022) [->li<-] Executive Vice President Applications at ASML (2013\u20132018) [->li<-] Management positions in marketing and product management at ASML (2008\u20132013) [->li<-] Director of Marketing at KLA Tencor (2003\u20132008) [->li<-] Global Product Manager at Applied Materials (1997\u20132001) [->li<-] Chair of the Supervisory Board of the Maastricht University Medical Center+ (2020\u2013current) [->li<-] Professor of Auditing at the Free University of Amsterdam (current) [->li<-] Member of the Supervisory Board of the Dutch National Bank (2018\u2013current) [->li<-] Member strategic committee Mistral AI (2025\u2013current) [->li<-] Global Vice Chair and member of the Executive Board of Deloitte Touche Tohmatsu, Ltd (2012\u20132018) \u00a0 [->li<-] CEO of Deloitte Holding BV (2005\u20132012) [->li<-] Audit Partner at Deloitte Netherlands (1996\u20132018) [->li<-] Various positions at Alstom including General Manager Hydro Business and Vice President Thermal Products Manufacturing at Alstom (1996\u20132009) [->li<-] Various positions at the French Ministry of Trade and Industry (1988\u20131996) [->li<-] Executive Vice President Customer Support at ASML (2018\u20132023) [->li<-] Senior Vice President of Global Manufacturing at Micron (2012\u20132018) [->li<-] Vice President of Worldwide Fabs at Micron (1987\u20132018) [->li<-] Vice President Supply Chain at Micron (2009\u20132012) [->li<-] \u00a0 [->li<-] Executive Vice President Applications Business (2018\u20132023) [->li<-] CEO Cymer Light Source division (2015\u20132018) [->li<-] General manager at Brion (2008\u20132015) [->li<-] Vice President of Marketing and Operations at MEMX Inc (2002\u20132006) [->li<-] Director of Manufacturing Engineering at Onetta (2000\u20132002) [->li<-] Director of Operations at Johnson & Johnson (1996\u20132000) [->li<-] Executive Vice President and Chief Technology Officer (2025\u2013current) \u00a0 [->li<-] Executive Vice President Applications (2023\u20132026) \u00a0 [->li<-] Executive Vice President EUV NXE (2021\u20132023) \u00a0 [->li<-] Various senior leadership positions in product and program management (2005\u20132021) \u00a0"]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] "]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Board of Management"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Christophe Fouquet [->h2<-] Roger Dassen [->h2<-] Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Schneider-Maunoury [->h2<-] Wayne Allan [->h2<-] Jim Koonmen [->h2<-] Marco Pieters\u00a0 [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] Rules of procedure [->h3<-] Remuneration [->h3<-] Supervisory Board [->h3<-] Annual reports [->h3<-] Shareholders"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] "]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] Our executives set and achieve the company\u2019s objectives, strategy and policies, and manage general affairs. [->span<-] President and Chief Executive Officer [->span<-] Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer [->span<-] Executive Vice President and Chief Operations Officer [->span<-] Executive Vice President and Chief Strategic Sourcing & Procurement Officer [->span<-] Executive Vice President and Chief Customer Officer [->span<-] Executive Vice President and Chief Technology Officer [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Overseeing and advising our Board of Management on general business issues and overall company direction [->p<-] Our Supervisory Board members are experienced business and technology professionals from around the world. [->p<-] In addition to overseeing business activities, they keep a keen eye on risk management, company culture, corporate social responsibility and the company\u2019s relationship with shareholders, and safeguard our integrity in reporting and compliance. [->p<-] The Supervisory Board meets at least four times per year. [->p<-] Danish national, 1958. Nils has been a member of the Supervisory Board since 2023 (term expires in 2027). [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Nils is currently the chairman\u00a0Scan Global Logistics A/S. From 2015 until May 2024, he served as a non-executive director at Unilever Plc and was appointed as Chair as per 2019. Nils was the chairman of the supervisory board of Akzo Nobel NV. He has also served as the group chief executive of A.P. M\u00f8ller\u2013M\u00e6rsk and held various management positions, including president and chief executive officer, at Carlsberg and Carlsberg Breweries.\u00a0 [->p<-] American national, 1961. Terri has been a member of the Supervisory Board since 2018 (third term expires in 2028). [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Terri is a trustee and member of several boards. Previously, Terri was President and CEO at W.L. Gore & Associates, having worked at Gore since 1983 in various management roles. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Belgian national, 1965. Birgit has been a member of the Supervisory Board since 2021 (second term expires in 2029). [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Birgit has an extensive background in finance and lastly was the CFO of Sonova Holding. She has held several CFO roles in the past as well as various management positions in finance at Johnson & Johnson, Heineken, Tenneco and Reed Elsevier.\u00a0As per February 1, 2025, she has been appointed as Non-Executive Director of AstraZeneca PLC. [->p<-] American national, 1961. Mark has been a member of the Supervisory Board since 2020 (second term expires in 2028). [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Mark has worked in the semiconductor industry for close to four decades. From 2012 until 2017, Mark was CEO of Micron Technology Inc, having joined the company in 1984. [->p<-] British national, 1961. Warren has been a member of the Supervisory Board since 2020 (second term expires in 2028). [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Warren is the former CEO of Rolls-Royce Group PLC and is currently Chair of the Board of Directors of NATS Holdings Ltd., the UK\u2019s National Air Traffic Service, and serves as non-executive director of Tokamak Energy Ltd. and ITM Power plc.\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Dutch national, 1968. Karien has been a member of the Supervisory Board since 2025 (term expires in 2029). [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Karien van Gennip brings extensive leadership experience across professional services, financial services, and public policy. She has served as Minister of Social Affairs and Employment in the Dutch government, CEO of Dutch healthcare insurer VGZ, and CEO of ING France. Earlier in her career, she was State Secretary of Economic Affairs, Minister for Foreign Trade, and held roles at McKinsey&Company and the Dutch Authority for Financial Markets. She has an educational background in physics from Delft University of Technology and holds an MBA from INSEAD.\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Dutch national, 1959. Jack has been a member of the Supervisory Board since 2023 (term expires in 2027). [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Among other roles, Jack is currently a member of the Supervisory Board, Chair of the Audit Committee and member of the ESG Committee at Royal Boskalis Westminster NV. In addition, he is the Chair of the Board of the Dutch Association of Listed Companies (VEUO). Previously, he held various management positions in finance at Royal Vopak NV, PricewaterhouseCoopers and the Dutch Ministry of Finance.\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Singaporean national, 1963. Benjamin has been a member of the Supervisory Board since 2026 (first term expires in 2030).\u00a0 [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Benjamin has extensive experience in the\u202felectronics and semiconductor industries, having held various board and executive positions throughout\u202fhis career. He currently serves as a Supervisory Board member at Comet AG and he is a member of the International Board of Semi Inc. Benjamin served as Chairman of the Board of Management, President and CEO for ASM\u202fInternational N.V. from 2020 until 2024. Benjamin holds a degree in electronic engineering from Tohoku University in Japan.\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Belgian national, 1971. An has been a member of the Supervisory Board since 2022 (second term expires in 2030). [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] An is CEO and member of the Board of Directors of Barco NV since September 1, 2024, after having served as a co-CEO and member of the Board of Directors since October 1 , 2021. Prior to that, An was R&D director at IBM Semiconductor and Executive Vice President at the research institute imec in Belgium. Furthermore, An was CTO and Executive Vice President Electronic and Electro-Optical Materials at Umicore. [->p<-] Assisting in overseeing the integrity and quality of our financial reporting and the effectiveness of risk management and controls. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Jack de Kreij (Chair) [->p<-] Nils Andersen [->p<-] Birgit Conix [->p<-] Warren East [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] The members of the Audit Committee are all independent, non-executive members of the Supervisory Board. The Audit Committee reviews ASML's financial reports, internal controls procedures, internal audit disclosures and compliance on a regular basis. The committee meets at least four times per year and always meets before the publication of financial results. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] For full details of the responsibilities of the Audit Committee see\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0of the\u00a0 [->p<-] . [->p<-] Overseeing the development and implementation of remuneration policies. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Terri Kelly (Chair) [->p<-] Karien van Gennip\u00a0 [->p<-] Jack de Kreij [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] The Remuneration Committee is responsible for preparing the Remuneration Policy for the ASML Board of Management, overseeing the development and implementation of compensation and benefit programs for members of the Board of Management, and determining the remuneration packages for individual Board of Management members. The Remuneration Committee meets at least twice per year and more often when necessary. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] For full details of the responsibilities of the Remuneration Committee see\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0of the\u00a0 [->p<-] . [->p<-] Assisting with the preparation of the selection criteria and appointment procedures for the Supervisory Board and Board of Management. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Nils Andersen (Chair) [->p<-] Mark Durcan [->p<-] Warren East [->p<-] Terri Kelly [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] The Selection and Nomination Committee assists the Supervisory Board in relation to its responsibilities over the composition and functioning of the Supervisory Board and the Board of Management. The Selection and Nomination Committee meets at least twice per year and more often if necessary. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] For full details of the responsibilities of the Selection and Nomination Committee see\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0of the\u00a0 [->p<-] . [->p<-] Providing advice with respect to our technology plans required to execute the business strategy. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Mark Durcan (Chair) [->p<-] Warren East [->p<-] Benjamin Loh [->p<-] An Steegen [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] The Technology Committee is responsible for assessing risk and investigating potential strategies, and they also look into technical resources and technology and product roadmaps. They then use their assessments to advise the rest of the Supervisory Board in these areas. The Technology Committee meets at least twice per year and more often if necessary. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] For full details of the responsibilities of the Technology Committee see\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0of the\u00a0 [->p<-] . [->p<-] Overseeing the ESG strategy and performance aimed at sustainable, long-term value creation. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Birgit Conix (Chair) [->p<-] Karien van Gennip [->p<-] Benjamin Loh [->p<-] An Steegen [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] The ESG Committee is responsible for overseeing the ESG strategy of ASML, as well as its execution and performance. The ESG Committee meets at least twice per year and more often if necessary. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] For full details of the responsibilities of the ESG Committee see\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0of the\u00a0 [->p<-] . [->p<-] Find out more about how the Supervisory Board is appointed, operates and makes decisions. [->p<-] All current members of the Supervisory Board are considered fully independent as defined by the Dutch Corporate Governance Code. [->p<-] Rules of Procedure Supervisory Board [->p<-] Profile of the Supervisory Board [->p<-] Supervisory Board Rotation Schedule [->p<-] At the AGM, ASML shareholders determine the remuneration of the members of the Supervisory Board based on the Supervisory Board\u2019s proposal and according to the Remuneration Policy adopted at the AGM on April 26, 2023. For more details, see the Supervisory Board Remuneration Policy and the Remuneration Report below. [->p<-] ASML Remuneration Policy Supervisory Board [->p<-] ASML Supervisory Board Remuneration [->p<-] 2025 Remuneration Report (US GAAP)"]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] The Board of Management sets and achieves ASML's objectives, strategy and policies, and manages general affairs. [->div<-] Read all our annual reports, explore our financial results and highlights [->div<-] We maintain a long-term commitment to our shareholders and value their input during annual meetings"]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] Chairman of the Board of Scan Global Logistics A/S (current) [->li<-] Chairman of the Board\u00a0\u00a0and non-executive director of Unilever Plc (2015\u20132024) [->li<-] Chairman of AkzoNobel NV (2018\u20132023) [->li<-] Group Chief Executive of A.P. M\u00f8ller\u2013M\u00e6rsk (2007\u20132016) [->li<-] President and Chief Executive Officer Carlsberg and Carlsberg Breweries (2001\u20132007)\u00a0 [->li<-] Member of the Board of Directors of United Rentals, Inc (current) [->li<-] Chair of the Board of Trustees of the University of Delaware (current) [->li<-] Trustee of the Nem