 [->li<-] Various leadership roles at ING Group, including Director of European and International Affairs and CEO of ING France (2008\u20132020) [->li<-] Member of the House of Representatives, the Netherlands (2006\u20132008) [->li<-] Secretary of State of Economic Affairs, Minister for Foreign Trade of the Netherlands, the Netherlands (2003\u20132007) [->li<-] Director Supervision, Authority for Financial Markets, the Netherlands (2002\u20132003) [->li<-] Consultant at McKinsey&Company (1996\u20132002) [->li<-] Member of the Supervisory Board of Royal Boskalis Westminster NV (current) [->li<-] Chairman of the Board of the Dutch Association of Listed Companies (VEUO) (current) [->li<-] Vice Chairman of the Supervisory Board and Chairman of the Audit Committee of Wolters Kluwer NV (2020\u20132026) \u00a0 [->li<-] Member of the Supervisory Board of TomTom NV (2017\u20132025) [->li<-] CFO and Vice Chairman of the Executive Board of Royal Vopak NV (2010\u20132018) and CFO and a member of the Executive Board of Royal Vopak NV (2003\u20132010) [->li<-] Various management positions as (Senior) Partner at PricewaterhouseCoopers (1986\u20132003) [->li<-] Dutch Ministry of Finance (1980\u20131986)\u00a0 [->li<-] Supervisory Board member at Umicore N.V. (2026\u2013present) [->li<-] Supervisory Board member at Comet AG (2024\u2013present) [->li<-] Member of the International Board of Semi\u202fInc.\u202f(2023\u2013present) [->li<-] Multiple non-executive and Supervisory Board positions, including\u202fat ASMPT Ltd. (2020\u20132024), Kriya B.V. (2018\u20132020), Schneeberger (2009\u20132011, 2018\u20132020), Liteq B.V. (2015\u20132017), Schweiter Technologies AG (2006\u20132009) [->li<-] EVP WW Sales and Marketing\u202fand member of the Board of Management at VAT Vacuum Valves AG (2015\u20132017) [->li<-] Various executive\u202fpositions at FEI Company, including Chief Operating Officer (2007\u20132013) [->li<-] Leadership positions at Veeco\u202fInstruments, Inc. (2005\u20132007) and Oerlikon Corporation (1998\u20132005)\u00a0 [->li<-] CEO of Barco NV (current) [->li<-] CTO and EVP Electronic and Electro-Optical materials at Umicore (2018\u20132021) [->li<-] EVP Semiconductor Technology & Systems at imec (2010\u20132018) [->li<-] R&D Director at IBM Semiconductors (2000\u20132010)"]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] Members [->strong<-] Annex E [->strong<-] Members [->strong<-] Annex F [->strong<-] Members [->strong<-] Annex G [->strong<-] Members [->strong<-] Annex H [->strong<-] Members [->strong<-] Annex I"]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Supervisory Board"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Nils Andersen [->h2<-] Terri Kelly [->h2<-] Birgit Conix [->h2<-] Mark Durcan [->h2<-] Warren East [->h2<-] Karien van Gennip [->h2<-] Jack de Kreij [->h2<-] Benjamin Loh\u00a0 [->h2<-] An Steegen [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] Supervisory Board committees [->h3<-] Additional information [->h3<-] Remuneration [->h3<-] Board of Management [->h3<-] Annual reports [->h3<-] Shareholders"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Audit Committee [->h4<-] Remuneration Committee [->h4<-] Selection and Nomination Committee [->h4<-] Technology Committee [->h4<-] ESG Committee [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] ASML\u2019s Supervisory Board is composed of nine members. Nils Andersen became the Supervisory Board\u2019s chair in 2023. Members of the Supervisory Board are appointed for a term of up to four years and may be reappointed twice."]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 111 [->span<-] Chair of the Supervisory Board [->span<-] Vice Chair of the Supervisory Board [->span<-] The Supervisory Board currently has five standing committees. The Supervisory Board has assigned some of its tasks and responsibilities to its committees, but the Supervisory Board remains responsible for all decisions, including those made by Supervisory Board committees. See the\u00a0 [->span<-] \u00a0for full details on the Supervisory Board and the committees. [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] Chair of the Selection & Nomination Committee [->em<-] \ufeffMember of the Audit Committee [->em<-] Chair of the Remuneration Committee [->em<-] Member of the Selection and Nomination Committee [->em<-] Chair of the ESG Committee [->em<-] Member of the Audit Committee [->em<-] Chair of the Technology Committee [->em<-] Member of the Selection and Nomination Committee [->em<-] Member of the Audit Committee [->em<-] Member of the Technology Committee [->em<-] Member of the ESG Committee  [->em<-] Member of the Remuneration Committee [->em<-] Chair of the Audit Committee [->em<-] Member of the Remuneration Committee"]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] We maintain a long-term commitment to our shareholders and value their input during annual meetings [->p<-] A share in the company means a voice in its governance. Shareholders are invited to attend our annual general meetings, vote on important topics, and raise any issues or questions they might have. [->p<-] At our annual general meeting (AGM), the Board of Management reports on the past year\u2019s activities. In addition to the management report and financial statements, the dividend policy and the remuneration report are discussed, as well as any other topics on the agenda. Find out more about our most recent AGMs here. [->p<-] Read about our stock exchange listings, share structure, see our major shareholders and links to other important information. [->p<-] At our investor days (held every two years), we inform shareholders, analysts and other stakeholders about our long-term strategy and financial model. [->p<-] Policy regarding Bilateral Contacts with Shareholders [->p<-] Take a tour of our annual reports to find out more about our performance and achievements, or download full reports."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] The Board of Management sets and achieves ASML's objectives, strategy and policies, and manages general affairs. [->div<-] Meet our Supervisory Board members, who oversee and advise ASML\u2019s Board of Management. [->div<-] We release annual and quarterly financial results to ensure investors, both current and potential, are kept informed."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] "]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Shareholders"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Shareholder meetings [->h2<-] ASML shares [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] Investor days [->h3<-] Annual Report [->h3<-] Board of Management [->h3<-] Supervisory Board [->h3<-] Financial results"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] Shareholders play an important role in ASML\u2019s governance. Next to the Board of Management and the Supervisory Board, shareholders participate in our general meetings, held at least once a year. [->h5<-] Policy regarding Bilateral Contacts with Shareholders"]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 34 [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] See our latest reports [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Committed to ethical behavior and speaking up [->p<-] Our Code of Conduct (Code) is based on the\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0of challenge, collaborate and care. These values are part of a shared belief system within ASML that defines who we are. [->p<-] The Code influences how we make decisions and guides us in our interactions with colleagues, customers, suppliers, shareholders and society as a whole. The Code helps us maintain the highest standard of ethics, integrity and respect. [->p<-] Our ethics program offers the necessary support, advice, training, and communication to enable employees and others to understand and follow our Code. We encourage and enable anyone to\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0if they observe behavior that violates our Code. [->p<-] Code of Conduct  [->p<-] Our Speak Up & Non-retaliation Policy allows anyone to report issues with respect to our Code. We are committed to an open culture of trust and honest communication, where violations of the Code are not tolerated. People who speak up will be protected for raising concerns about suspected misconduct in good faith. Reports will be treated confidentially and parties can report concerns anonymously. [->p<-] How to Speak Up [->p<-] The Ethics Office at ASML can be emailed directly at\u00a0 [->p<-] . Alternatively, our Speak Up service enables anyone to call a local telephone number or send a message through an independent website by following the link from the name of the location in which you are located. Speak Up offers the possibility to report anonymously. [->p<-] ASML - Speak Up Policy 2021 [->p<-] At ASML, we conduct business on the basis of fairness, good faith and integrity, and we expect the same from our partners and suppliers. ASML became a member of the Responsible Business Alliance (RBA) in 2011 and adopted the RBA Code of Conduct, which provides guidance in four critical areas: labor, health & safety, environment and ethics. To reinforce our commitment to the supplier network, we expect our key suppliers and their suppliers to comply with the RBA Code of Conduct and to develop their own strategies, policies and processes to follow it. [->p<-] We are committed to conducting business with business fairness, integrity and respect for the law and our values. Our Anti-Bribery & Anti-Corruption Policy details our commitment and the measures we take to prevent bribery and corruption at ASML. The Policy is designed to help employees and affiliates understand the internal and external requirements to report any suspicious or actual anti-corruption behavior and to help comply with these requirements. [->p<-] ASML - Anti-Bribery & Anti-Corruption Policy  [->p<-] ASML recognizes that responsible AI and related practices are fundamental aspects of AI innovation. At ASML, we put responsible AI into practice through appropriate governance and alignment with global regulations and standards. Find out more about  [->p<-] . [->p<-] We are committed to fair competition and fairness in dealing with our business partners including suppliers, co-developers, customers and other industry peers. ASML does not condone any form of conduct that is considered illegal under applicable competition laws or is contrary to our Code. Our Competition Law Compliance Policy demonstrates our ongoing commitment to ensuring compliance with applicable competition laws and our Code. [->p<-] ASML Competition Law Compliance Policy [->p<-] ASML is committed to respecting universal human rights and honoring our Code and values. Our Human Rights Policy applies to all our organizations and subsidiaries around the world, as well as to our suppliers. [->p<-] ASML - Human Rights Policy [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Our Human Rights Policy is in line with various key international human rights standards and guidelines, including: [->p<-] We also make sure that within our value chain human rights are: [->p<-] \u00a0As a company we aim to avoid any human rights violations in operations in which we have direct or indirect involvement . [->p<-] We frequently assess actual and potential human rights risks, both in our own operations and in our supply chain. We educate employees about the importance of human rights and cooperate with the international community and our business partners in preventing human rights violations. [->p<-] \u00a0We ensure that any (potential) human rights violations within our value chain can be reported to ASML (through our Speak Up & Non-retaliation Policy) and that all reported incidents are addressed. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] The California Transparency in Supply Chains Act (2010) and the United Kingdom (UK) Modern Slavery Act 2015, Chapter 30, Part 6, Provision 54 require companies to disclose their efforts to eradicate slavery and human trafficking from any of their supply chains and in any part of their business. ASML is committed to ensuring that all levels of its supply chain comply with the highest international standards of fairness, sustainability and ethical conduct, including a strict prohibition on forced and involuntary labor and illegal trafficking in persons. [->p<-] According to Dutch law, members of ASML\u2019s Board of Management and Supervisory Board are required to notify the Dutch Authority Financial Markets (AFM) of any ASML financial instruments they hold or that are held on their behalf, as well as any transactions in those holdings that they make or that are made on their behalf. [->p<-] The AFM publishes all reported transactions on its\u00a0 [->p<-] . [->p<-] All employees, including members of ASML\u2019s Board of Management and Supervisory Board, are bound by ASML\u2019s Insider Trading Rules. [->p<-] ASML - Insider Trading Rules"]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] DOWNLOAD [->div<-] KPMG NV has been ASML\u2019s external auditor since reporting year 2016. ASML also has an internal audit department. [->div<-] We maintain a long-term commitment to our shareholders and value their input during annual meetings [->div<-] Browse ASML\u2019s corporate governance policies and archives."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] China [->td<-] +86 4001200809 [->td<-] France [->td<-] +33 971079402 [->td<-] Italy [->td<-] +39 0694803200 [->td<-] Malaysia [->td<-] +60 (0)1548771204 [->td<-] Netherlands [->td<-] +31 (0)852081789 [->td<-] Singapore [->td<-] +65 31580506 [->td<-] South Korea [->td<-] \u00a0+82 237005103 [->td<-] Taiwan [->td<-] +886 00801128172 [->td<-] UK [->td<-] +44 141 673 6062 [->td<-] USA [->td<-] +1 203 769 9406 [->td<-] Germany [->td<-] +49 3083792500 [->td<-] Israel [->td<-] +972 77 223 0423 [->td<-] Ireland [->td<-] +35 3818001476 [->td<-] Japan [->td<-] +81 (0)345104476 [->td<-] Belgium [->td<-] +32 784 80109"]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] ILO Declaration on Fundamental Principles and Rights at Work [->li<-] UN Declaration of Human Rights [->li<-] UN Global Compact [->li<-] OECD Guidelines for Multinational Enterprises [->li<-] Code of Conduct of the Responsible Business Alliance (RBA)"]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] Respected: [->strong<-] Protected:\u00a0 [->strong<-] Remediated: [->strong<-] California Supply Chains Act and UK Modern Slavery Act Disclosure"]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Code of Conduct"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] Speak Up & Non-retaliation Policy [->h3<-] Code of Conduct for Suppliers [->h3<-] Anti-Bribery & Anti-Corruption Policy [->h3<-] Responsible AI [->h3<-] Competition Law Compliance Policy [->h3<-] Human Rights Policy [->h3<-] Insider Trading Rules [->h3<-] Auditors [->h3<-] Shareholders [->h3<-] Governance downloads"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] "]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 59 [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Submit your concern here [->span<-] Location [->span<-] Phone number [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Transparency is important to us. Read about our\u00a0 [->span<-] . [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] A systematic approach in a dynamic environment [->p<-] Enterprise risk management is a continuous process. Its related activities are repeated regularly to identify and address risks, ensuring outcomes are relevant for effective decision-making. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] We adopt a holistic approach combining both top-down (company-level) and bottom-up (organization and process-level) perspectives. This helps us identify, evaluate and manage risks at the right level. We continuously seek to improve our ERM process based on learnings, developments and best practices.\u00a0 [->p<-] We deploy our ERM framework through a well-defined governance structure. ASML\u2019s Risk and Business Assurance team, which reports to the CFO, coordinates the ERM process and associated activities across ASML. \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] ASML sets standards for risk management to identify, manage and monitor risks, supporting leadership in driving continuous, sustainable growth.\u00a0 [->p<-] Many risks have the potential to impact our business and it is important to understand their nature. We assess risks using the ASML risk universe \u2013 a consolidated view of the risk categories that may have an adverse effect in achieving our business objectives. We review and update our risk universe frequently, taking into account a broad range of internal and external information sources, such as macroeconomic and industry trends, relevant guidelines and legislation, and stakeholders\u2019 needs and expectations.\u00a0"]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] ASML is committed to upholding ethical behavior. Download our policies and learn more. [->div<-] There\u2019s value in being ahead of the curve. Learn how we make technological advances and generate opportunities. [->div<-] Read all our annual reports, explore our financial results and highlights"]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] "]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] How we manage risk"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] Our risk management process [->h3<-] Risk management governance structure [->h3<-] Risk factors [->h3<-] Code of Conduct [->h3<-] Why invest in ASML [->h3<-] Annual reports"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] Dynamics in the global semiconductor industry present both opportunities and risks. ASML manages risk through an enterprise risk management (ERM) framework that integrates risk management into our daily business activities and strategic planning.\u00a0"]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 28 [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] At the Annual General Meeting (AGM) held in 2025, \u00a0PricewaterhouseCoopers Accountants N.V. (PwC) was appointed as the external auditor to issue an independent opinion on ASML\u2019s financial statements for reporting year 2026. PwC\u2019s first appointment as the external auditor was made at the 2023 AGM, with effect from the reporting year 2025. Furthermore, at the 2025 AGM, PwC was appointed as the external assurance provider for the sustainability statements for the reporting years 2025 and 2026.\u00a0 [->p<-] The external auditor\u2019s performance and work completed for ASML and all its subsidiaries are evaluated on an annual basis between the Audit Committee and the Board of Management, and the outcome is reported to the Supervisory Board and disclosed in the annual report and communicated to the General Meeting. The outcome of the annual evaluation is taken into consideration when assessing the potential reappointment of the external auditor. [->p<-] At least once a year, the Audit Committee and the external auditor discuss their relationship with each other, as well as the external auditor\u2019s relationship with the Board of Management. The Audit Committee, on behalf of the Supervisory Board, is responsible for approving the external auditor\u2019s budget, fees and audit plan, which are determined annually. [->p<-] PricewaterhouseCoopers Accountants N.V. [->p<-] Thomas R. Malthusstraat 5 [->p<-] 1066 JR Amsterdam [->p<-] The Netherlands [->p<-] Information on external auditor fees is made available annually in the  [->p<-] . [->p<-] ASML has an internal audit function. The internal audit function reports directly to the Supervisory Board\u2019s Audit Committee and the Board of Management. Internal auditing is an independent and objective assurance and consulting activity guided by a philosophy of adding value and improving ASML\u2019s operations. \u00a0The internal audit function helps the company accomplish its objectives by bringing a systematic and disciplined approach to evaluating and improving the effectiveness of risk management, control and governance processes. [->p<-] The establishment of these processes is the responsibility of ASML\u2019s Board of Management. While maintaining an independent position, the internal audit function cooperates with the Board of Management to ensure risks are taken in a controlled way. The internal audit function provides assurance services to the Board of Management and the Audit Committee. The internal audit function\u2019s advisory role is primarily the result of the recommendations included in internal audit reports addressing specific internal control weaknesses. Other advisory services are assessed against criteria meant to preserve the internal audit\u2019s independence and objectivity."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] We maintain a long-term commitment to our shareholders and value their input during annual meetings [->div<-] ASML is committed to upholding ethical behavior. Download our policies and learn more. [->div<-] Browse ASML\u2019s corporate governance policies and archives."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] PricewaterhouseCoopers Accountants N.V. has been ASML\u2019s external auditor since the reporting year 2025."]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Auditors"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] External auditor [->h3<-] Internal audit function [->h3<-] Shareholders [->h3<-] Code of Conduct [->h3<-] Governance downloads"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] "]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Find out more about our performance and achievements over the years. [->p<-] Find out more about our performance and achievements over the years."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] Learn about ASML\u2019s risk management framework and how risk influences our strategy. [->div<-] ASML is committed to upholding ethical behavior. Download our policies and learn more. [->div<-] KPMG NV has been ASML\u2019s external auditor since reporting year 2016. ASML also has an internal audit department."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] "]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Downloads"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] How we manage risk [->h3<-] Code of Conduct [->h3<-] Auditors"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Annual reports [->h4<-] Shareholder meetings [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] "]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] Downloads"]], ["span", ["[->span<-] Annual reports [->span<-] Shareholder meetings [->span<-] \tArticles of Association [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Rules of Procedure Board of Management [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] ASML Remuneration Policy Board of Management [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Rules of Procedure Supervisory Board [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] \tASML Remuneration Policy Supervisory Board [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] \tASML Supervisory Board Remuneration [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Profile of the Supervisory Board [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Supervisory Board Rotation Schedule [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] 2025 Remuneration Report (US GAAP) [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Code of Conduct [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Speak Up & Non-retaliation Policy [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] ASML Anti-Bribery and Anti-Corruption Policy [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] ASML Human Rights Policy [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] ASML Competition Law Compliance Policy [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] ASML Insider Trading Rules [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Policy regarding Bilateral Contacts with Shareholders [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] ASML Stakeholder Engagement Policy [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] ASML Group Diversity and Inclusion Policy [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Clawback Policy - under US/NASDAQ rules [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] ASML Global Advocacy Report 2025 [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] ASML Worldwide ISO14001 PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] ASML Commitment Letter RBA PDF [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Conflict Minerals Report 2025 [->span<-] PDF [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Our products enable our customers to create advanced microchips. That matters to us because those advanced chips then enable exciting new digital technologies, including AI, that can help tackle some of society\u2019s toughest challenges. \u00a0 [->p<-] At ASML, we are energized by compelling new applications for digital technologies - in healthcare, education, energy and mobility. We are inspired by their potential for positive impact, on people and the planet. [->p<-] At the same time, these advancements bring new challenges. For example, AI growth brings concerns about energy consumption by data centers. To address this, there will need to be both more efficient AI models and improved semiconductors. Our customers are creating ever more energy-efficient chips, and we are providing our lithography innovation to support the 2D shrink and 3D integration required to do this. Breakthroughs in chip energy efficiency will rely on cooperation across the semiconductor  [->p<-] . \u00a0 \u00a0 [->p<-] Our customers are also increasing production of both advanced and mainstream microchips, to meet growing demand. Companies across the semiconductor value chain are working together to help curb the resulting increase in energy use and emissions. Choosing ASML\u2019s EUV lithography moves the manufacturing process from multi-patterning to single patterning, and fewer steps in the customer fab creates environmental benefits. Plus, we are working to make all our systems more energy efficient. [->p<-] We are further increasing the energy efficiency of the systems we produce, as well as those we have already installed at our customer sites. Each of our product families has an energy-saving road map, with adjustments having the potential to make a big difference when scaled through customer adoption. \u00a0 [->p<-] From sleep modes, to high-temperature cooling water, to reuse of hydrogen, our engineers are collaborating with customers and suppliers to innovate practical solutions.\u00a0 [->p<-] In our ASML manufacturing and buildings, we have chosen renewable electricity, and we drive continuous improvement in energy saving. From optimized clean room controls, to reuse of waste heat, to on-site hydrogen generation. In transport, an increasing number of shipments to customers are now by ocean rather than air. We ask our suppliers to commit to saving energy and reducing emissions too, working together to achieve shared goals. [->p<-] Servicing and repairing installed systems, to extend their already long life, is central to our customer offer. We are now repairing more parts locally, closer to the customer, to reduce cycle times and cut emissions. \u00a0 [->p<-] Efficient use of materials is a priority for us. We focus on driving down waste and increasing reuse of returned materials before we use new. We manage end-of-life materials, so that they are either recycled or responsibly disposed of. [->p<-] Treating people with care has always been fundamental to us - in our company, in our supply chain and in our communities. We take steps to ensure the safety and well-being of our employees, and a commitment to  [->p<-]  helps drive our innovation and business success. Due diligence in how people are treated is part of our relationship with suppliers. We listen and respond to people who live near our operations, especially when we grow our footprint. [->p<-] We invest in advancing semiconductor innovation, to support our industry\u2019s development and its contribution to tackling societal challenges. We also invest in issues that matter most to our neighbors and colleagues, and that create lasting benefits. \u00a0 [->p<-] Our  [->p<-]  ranges from affordable housing, to early-years science education, to green spaces, and arts and sports programs. We are proud to support our employees in their own contributions, through time off work for volunteering and matching of donations. [->p<-] We engage with our stakeholders on focus topics for our sustainability program, and organize through themes, each with transparent targets. One of our key ambitions is to be greenhouse gas neutral throughout our value chain by 2040, and this is supported by a detailed Climate Transition Plan, including interim milestones. ASML\u2019s senior management regularly reviews performance, which is integrated into long-term leadership incentives. Find related  [->p<-] ."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] Read all our annual reports, explore our financial results and highlights [->div<-] ASML is an innovation leader in the semiconductor industry. Find out what we do and why we do it. [->div<-] Our shareholders, Supervisory Board and Board of Management all play an important role in ASML\u2019s governance."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] "]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Sustainability"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] Inspired by technology\u00a0 [->h3<-] Energy use and emissions [->h3<-] Chip manufacturing footprint\u00a0 [->h3<-] Our products in customer fabs\u00a0 [->h3<-] Our operations and supply chain\u00a0 [->h3<-] Circularity\u00a0 [->h3<-] Prioritizing people\u00a0 [->h3<-] Giving funds, resources and time\u00a0 [->h3<-] Governance and reporting\u00a0 [->h3<-] Annual reports [->h3<-] About ASML [->h3<-] Governance"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Find out what sustainability means to us at ASML and what concrete actions we are taking together with our customers, suppliers and partners. [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] "]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 52 [->span<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] For details and data, see the sustainability highlights of our annual report [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] At ASML, we support our local communities through education, sports, arts and music, and other outreach activities [->p<-] As a global technology leader and employer, we play an active role in the communities we operate in. We partner with neighbors and local organizations to build meaningful relationships so that we can benefit from each other\u2019s growth and thrive together. Our  [->p<-]  is fundamental to our ESG sustainability strategy. [->p<-] We organize and support numerous initiatives that aim to share our enthusiasm and expertise in technology to inspire future generations. The ASML Junior Academy, our flagship education program, delivers fun and engaging STEM lessons for primary school classes in collaboration with Mad Science. We also participate in multiple educational events that promote career opportunities in technology, including\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0and\u00a0 [->p<-] . [->p<-] We collaborate with several organizations that have sports, arts and music initiatives in the communities where we work. For example,\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0in Amsterdam and Van Gogh Brabant to find new ways to preserve historic paintings. We also have a long-term partnership with the Muziekgebouw in Eindhoven, bringing our employees and community members together through a shared passion for the stage. [->p<-] We want to help strengthen our local communities, supporting initiatives that provide access to basic needs and help unlock the potential of disadvantaged community members. [->p<-] Our work includes supporting food banks, donating funds to charities and working with environmental organizations on conservation projects to care for those in need and protect our planet. We also recognize the power of volunteers to transform our communities and encourage employees to give back to their communities through our global volunteering program. [->p<-] We always welcome new opportunities to sponsor activities, initiatives or organizations that align with our community engagement focus areas of education, sports, arts and music, and local outreach. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] For questions related to ASML\u2019s community engagement activities, including education initiatives, outreach programs and local partnerships, please contact:  [->p<-] .\u00a0"]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] Get to know ASML and learn about our vision and mission, our history, and how we operate. [->div<-] ASML is an innovation leader in the semiconductor industry. Find out what we do and why we do it. [->div<-] Find out what sustainability means to us at ASML and what concrete actions we are taking together with our customers, suppliers and partners."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] "]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Community engagement"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] Company [->h3<-] About ASML [->h3<-] Sustainability"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Education [->h4<-] Sports, arts and music [->h4<-] Local outreach [->h4<-] Contact [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] "]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 38 [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] As the world moves closer to a fully digital future, we strive to improve the quality and accessibility of STEM (science, technology, engineering and math) education so that all members of society, especially children, have the opportunity to fulfill their potential. [->span<-] Find out more about education [->span<-] Culture is the invisible bond that unites people in a community. We support initiatives and organizations that strengthen those bonds and help open them up for newcomers. [->span<-] Find out more about sports, arts and music [->span<-] Find out more about local outreach [->span<-] Apply for support [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Fostering STEM education and inspiring future generations [->p<-] The  [->p<-]  provides primary schools with engaging, structured STEM lessons for children. These lessons are delivered by our partner,  [->p<-] . In a number of cases, ASML employees are also involved, contributing their expertise to enhance the learning experience. The program is active in Veldhoven, the Netherlands, and Wilton, United States, with the ambition to reach 190,000 children in the coming years. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Our STEMup program helps secondary schools strengthen STEM education for first and second year students. Working with a STEM coach from WisMon, schools can choose one of four STEM classes developed by ASML. The pilot, which runs in the Veldhoven area into 2025, is supported by local educational organizations: FutureBites, Junior IOT, de Maakotheek and de Ontdekfabriek. Findings will inform the planned expansion of the program. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Through the hybrid teaching initiative, our employees swap the cleanroom for the classroom to teach technical subjects in schools and universities. They also volunteer as STEM ambassadors, giving lectures in educational settings and hosting students who visit ASML campuses. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] We are involved in several\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0with our partners at the Van Gogh Museum and Van Gogh Brabant. We are developing educational materials for schools on Van Gogh\u2019s life and work, as well as the\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0which challenges students to follow in Van Gogh\u2019s footsteps by experimenting with color and light. [->p<-] During this week-long, annual event in the Brainport region, we promote enthusiasm and pride in technology to strengthen the Dutch high-tech sector. We participate in various events to inspire young people about technology and technological studies. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Many children lack access to tutoring, which widens the education gap for disadvantaged communities. To help close the gap, we launched the\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0in partnership with Center for Care and Spectrum Brabant. Through this program, our employees paired up with secondary school students to help them catch up on school subjects and make progress in their studies. [->p<-] In 2022, we partnered with the Van Gogh Museum, CommonWealth Magazine Foundation and Junyi Academy to localize our \u2018Mastermind and Masterpieces\u2019 program in Mandarin. 200 employees were trained as volunteers and STEM educators, leading UV light workshops in remote schools. [->p<-] We support the Shanghai Science and Technology Museum, which organizes the Shanghai Future Engineer Competition. We also sponsor the ASML Youth Maker and Hacker Science and Technology Innovation contest, in which approximately 80 schoolchildren participate each year. [->p<-] We support the Ocean Discovery Institute (ODI), whose mission is to use ocean science to empower young people. Through ODI, our employees participate in Q&A sessions for students to encourage them to grow their science knowledge. We also work with the Reuben H. Fleet Science Center and participate in the Fleet\u2019s Better Education for Women in Science and Engineering (BE WiSE) program, which provides STEM education to young girls in San Diego County. We have also supported the nonprofit Science Delivered, funding take-home STEM kits for students in lower socioeconomic schools. [->p<-] Get in touch with us to find out about upcoming events, or how your school could be involved in our STEM initiatives through sponsorship, by hosting a guest teacher or through a visit to ASML. [->p<-] These lessons are currently available only in the Netherlands. If you are a primary or secondary school teacher, please complete the request form."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] At ASML, we support our local communities through education, sports, arts and music, and local outreach activities [->div<-] Supporting initiatives and organizations that celebrate and strengthen the culture of our communities [->div<-] Strengthening communities, supporting access to basic needs and unlocking the potential of disadvantaged community members."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] Working with schools around the world [->strong<-] ASML Junior Academy\ufeff [->strong<-] STEMup [->strong<-] Hybrid teaching and STEM ambassadors [->strong<-] Van Gogh Museum and Van Gogh Brabant [->strong<-] The Netherlands [->strong<-] Dutch Technology Week [->strong<-] Inclusive Talent tutoring program [->strong<-] Asia [->strong<-] Taiwan [->strong<-] Chinese mainland [->strong<-] United States [->strong<-] San Diego"]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Education"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] Get in touch [->h3<-] Request a guest lesson from ASML [->h3<-] Community engagement [->h3<-] Sports, arts and music [->h3<-] Local outreach"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] Want to get your school involved or know what events are coming up?"]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 41 [->span<-] Today, technology forms the foundation of almost all industries. As a result, STEM (science, technology, engineering and math) education is crucial for helping young people thrive in an increasingly technological world. We\u2019re doing our part to share our science and technology knowledge, promote STEM initiatives and work hard to ensure that all young people have access to technical education to reach their potential. [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] Promoting curiosity and creativity [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] Partnering to inspire and empower [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] Supporting innovators and creators of the future [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] Email us [->span<-] Request a guest lesson from ASML [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Supporting initiatives where our community members can enjoy sports, arts, music and each other\u2019s company [->p<-] ASML supports PSV, together with five other companies from the Brainport region. The partnership is part of our social sports program, which aims to make sports widely available. As a well-known club in the Brainport area, PSV plays a key role in bringing people together during matches, fostering a strong sense of community.\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] As part of our commitment to making sports accessible to everyone in the community, we also run the ASML Community Lounge at the Philips stadium, home to PSV. Each year, we invite over 4,500 Brainport residents to attend a match there. These invitations go to those who may not otherwise have the opportunity to experience a live game, as well as to individuals who have made a special contribution to the region.\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] In 2026, we announced the extension of our sponsorship through the 2030\u20132031 season.\u00a0 [->p<-] We collaborate with the Van Gogh Museum in Amsterdam and Van Gogh Brabant to help\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0and legacy of Vincent Van Gogh, who, like ASML, hails from the Brabant region of the Netherlands. As part of our partnership, we helped expand the Van Gogh Village Museum in Nuenen where visitors can learn about light and how Vincent van Gogh experimented with it in his paintings. [->p<-] Because light is key to our work, we are a main partner and sponsor of the annual GLOW light art festival. This free event in Eindhoven, displays the works of famous national and international light artists throughout the city center over one week in November. Every year, almost 1 million visitors attend the festival. Not only do we commission an artist to create a piece of art to be displayed alongside other artists\u2019 work during the festival, but we also organize special events \u2013 such as guided tours in various languages \u2013 for international colleagues living in the Netherlands to help them feel at home and part of the local community. [->p<-] We partner with\u00a0 [->p<-] , the main concert hall in the city, which offers a wide selection of musical events and education. Once a year, the employees of ASML take to the stage, filling the hall with a diverse range of music genres \u2013 reflecting the diverse nature of the company \u2013 with our special annual event, ASML on Stage. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] For members of our Brainport community in the Netherlands, we also host Spotlight, an event that welcomes people from across the Brainport region to take the Muziekgebouw Eindhoven stage to celebrate music, express their passion in a performance, and learn from talented artists. Spotlight is one way we are giving back to our community and proving that everyone has something to offer."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] At ASML, we support our local communities through education, sports, arts and music, and local outreach activities [->div<-] ASML is an innovation leader in the semiconductor industry. Find out what we do and why we do it. [->div<-] Find out what it\u2019s like working at a semiconductor industry leader. Discover job benefits, clubs and events, and our culture."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] Sports [->strong<-] Arts [->strong<-] Music"]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Sports, arts and music"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] Community engagement [->h3<-] About ASML [->h3<-] Working at ASML"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] GLOW light art festival [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] "]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 41 [->span<-] Culture is an invisible bond that unites people. Sports, arts and music are culture made visible. By promoting various local organizations and initiatives, ASML helps to strengthen those bonds while building an appreciation for our communities\u2019 cultural expression. [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] Partnership with PSV soccer club [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Van Gogh Mu [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] seum and Van G\ufeffogh Brabant [->span<-] Van Gogh partnerships [->span<-] Photo: Jan Kees Steenman [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] ASML on Stage & Spotlight\ufeff [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] Find out more about spotlight [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Strengthening communities, supporting access to basic needs and unlocking the potential of disadvantaged community members [->p<-] As part of the\u00a0 [->p<-] , we help to strengthen the region and support local people who are struggling. Through this partnership, we participate in community activities to help tackle urgent social challenges in the region, for example by supporting services that provide budgeting and financial management advice for those in need. [->p<-] There is a significant housing shortage in the Brainport Eindhoven region of the Netherlands, which puts serious pressure on affordability. People with low to middle incomes struggle to find affordable homes, and ASML's growth adds to their challenge. In 2023, we launched our Affordable Housing project, which aims to help increase the number of affordable homes for everyone in the Brainport Eindhoven region, primarily by providing support for the construction of new homes. We run this project in collaboration with several external parties, such as housing corporations, municipalities and real estate developers. [->p<-] We take part in a variety of social initiatives. For example, we provide yearly donations to the local food banks around our Dutch headquarters. In addition, we support the Eindhoven homeless shelter\u00a0 [->p<-] , which provides accommodation and advice for homeless people, as well as\u00a0 [->p<-] , which organizes social activities and resources for children in poverty. We also facilitate regional activities that focus on building social connections and helping newcomers get acquainted with the region and local culture. Every year, we organize the \u2018Angel Tree\u2019: a collection of presents for children whose parents are clients of the local food bank. [->p<-] Every December in San Diego, our employees help package and sort food at our annual Food Sorting Night at the San Diego Food Bank. In Silicon Valley, we have partnered with Second Harvest of Silicon Valley for over a decade. Our local team hosts food drives and organizes volunteer groups to sort food at local warehouses throughout the year. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] We support the Family Giving Tree charity in Silicon Valley, collecting school supplies, backpacks and personalized holiday gifts across the year to be donated to disadvantaged families and individuals in the community. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] We support the Boys & Girls Clubs of Silicon Valley\u2019s summer enrichment programs, providing volunteers and funding for scholarships that offer lower-income students the opportunity to participate in STEM, sports, arts and wellness-focused summer camps. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] In Connecticut, we work with the Wilton Land Conservation Trust to improve open space amenities and restore biodiversity. We removed invasive plant species and planted native plants and trees to support birds and wildlife at the Eugenia Slaughter Native Wildflower Meadow and Schencks Island in Wilton. [->p<-] To help preserve and protect nearby nature, our teams in Asia participate in regular beach cleanups. Colleagues, along with their families and friends, put their appreciation for the environment into action by removing garbage from reservations and nature parks. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Over the holiday season, our Christmas Shoebox Project collects gifts that are prepared and wrapped by ASML employees. The shoeboxes are sent to children from economically disadvantaged families in remote areas, bringing a spark of holiday joy with each delivery. [->p<-] ASML aims to be a good corporate citizen and contribute to the current and future livability of our local communities. Even though biodiversity is not a material topic for ASML globally, we recognize its importance for local stakeholders. Our ambition is to prevent net loss of biodiversity and net deforestation resulting from our operations and building activity by preserving, safeguarding, restoring and enhancing our landscapes. Therefore, ASML assesses dependency and impact-related biodiversity risks. This assessment covers ASML\u2019s own operations. No major risks were identified. [->p<-] We always welcome new opportunities to sponsor activities, initiatives or organizations that align with our community engagement focus areas of education, sports, arts and music, and local outreach."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job"]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] \ufeffThe Netherlands [->strong<-] Brainport Eindhoven Partner Fund [->strong<-] Affordable Housing project [->strong<-] Other social initiatives [->strong<-] United States\ufeff [->strong<-] Food bank support [->strong<-] Family Giving Tree [->strong<-] Boys & Girls Clubs [->strong<-] Wilton Land Conservation Trust [->strong<-] Asia\ufeff [->strong<-] Beach cleanups [->strong<-] Holiday giving"]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Local outreach"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] "]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] Expanding access to basic needs and supporting our communities"]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 30 [->span<-] We are committed to doing our share as a socially conscious business in the communities we are a part of. By partnering with businesses and organizations in the regions around the world where ASML is located, we are building trust and contributing to our communities. [->span<-] Helping those in need and protecting the environment [->span<-] Caring for the planet and people [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] Green communities [->span<-] Apply for support [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Be a part of the tech company that\u2019s a part of everything [->p<-] Year founded [->p<-] Total employees (FTEs) [->p<-] Nationalities [->p<-] Locations [->p<-] 2025 annual figures [->p<-] Working at ASML is unlike working at any other company - even other high-tech companies. It's more extreme and more inspiring, no matter the field you're in. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] ASML offers opportunities for students and graduates in practically every technical field. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Work at ASML [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] We support both global big-name customers and fast-growing local customers with 12 customer support sites, two R&D centers, and one training center. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Japan is home to tech giants and major semiconductor players, with whom ASML collaborates closely. You can help to advance technology \u2013 and your career. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] ASML is headquartered in Veldhoven amid a thriving ecosystem of high-tech companies. Our headquarters is home to more than half of all our employees. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Our teams in South Korea work closely with Samsung and other customers and have five locations that include a global distribution center and 4 training centers. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] We have the largest ASML manufacturing site in Asia as well as two training centers, play an essential role in the rapidly growing e-beam market, and work closely with TSMC and major semiconductor fabs. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] With 14 customer support sites, two factories, and three R&D centers, our US locations service Intel and other customers and contribute to our holistic product portfolio. [->p<-] Discover what it\u2019s like to work at ASML. Dive into this interactive section to learn about compensation and benefits, well-being, volunteering and giving back to our communities, employee networks and sports clubs, exciting events, and learning and development. [->p<-] At ASML, we strive to create a safe and inclusive environment for all. We welcome unique voices, identities and experiences, and treat each person with care and respect. [->p<-] stories [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Culture & Values [->p<-] Work/life balance [->p<-] Senior Management [->p<-] Compensation and Benefits [->p<-] Career opportunities [->p<-] Diversity & Inclusion [->p<-] Visit our interview tips page to learn more about ASML\u2019s job application and interview [->p<-] process."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] > [->div<-] , [->div<-] > [->div<-] Our Germany locations, such as Berlin and Dresden, specialize in optical manufacturing technology, precision manufacturing, as well as software development and customer support. [->div<-] Faced with a complex issue, Anya Kish rose to the challenge by turning it into a growth opportunity [->div<-] Meet George Tao, who turns time constraints into team triumphs [->div<-] Meet Manisha Devi, who spearheaded the rollout of a new digital platform under pressure [->div<-] From accounting to relationship building, Manon Hendriks\u2019s career is full of growth and inspiration [->div<-] Meet Mark Bergkotte, who believes focusing on employees\u2019 health and well-being is the key to success [->div<-] Meet Ron Kool, who made a bold career transition to improve ASML\u2019s business processes [->div<-] With over 60 locations worldwide, we are a growing global force in the semiconductor industry. [->div<-] R&D, manufacturing, and customer support are the pillars of our organization, supported by our corporate functions. [->div<-] From a leaky wooden shed to a global force, ASML's journey in the semiconductor industry began in 1984."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-]  "]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Careers"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] ASML's Glassdoor rating [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] Our company culture [->h3<-] ASML at a glance [->h3<-] Organization [->h3<-] History"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Technology is a force for good. It connects us and changes how we live, work, and play. At the heart of it all is ASML. Most of the electronic devices you use daily are only possible because of our lithography systems. [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] "]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 42 [->span<-] More about working at ASML [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [