->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Discover how we conduct interviews at ASML, as well as tips and tricks that will help you make a lasting impression during your interview and set you up for success. [->p<-] Start by revamping your CV. Keep it clear and concise. Make sure it illustrates your strongest experiences and talents. Include your professional and academic achievements, and if needed include your portfolio. When listing your competencies, make sure to prepare concrete examples of how you applied your talents and skills in your current or past roles. [->p<-] Focus on finding the job opening that best matches your background and aspirations. But beyond that explore the many teams within ASML and discover which one is aligned the most with the way you enjoy working. Read the job description carefully and see how it matches with relevant experiences in your resume. [->p<-] Did you find a job that matches your skills and ambition? Hit the apply button and submit your resume via the ASML career portal. Once you successfully submit your application, you\u2019ll receive an email confirmation. You can always log in to your candidate portal to view the status of your job application. [->p<-] After you submit your application, our Talent Acquisition team will carefully review your profile. If there is a match, we\u2019ll contact you for a first introduction. [->p<-] \u201cGood preparation before any interview is key. It\u2019s not about having a super polished answer to all the questions but preparing responses for some questions in advance will help you build confidence. It will also decrease any anxiety that may impact your performance during an interview.\u201d [->p<-] In preparation for your interview, we recommend that you learn more about ASML by browsing our website, connecting with us via our social media and reading relevant articles. In addition, you can learn more about  [->p<-]  and what our  [->p<-]  do.\u00a0 [->p<-] If you\u2019re invited to continue with the interview process, you may be asked to complete a talent exploration questionnaire before your second interview. The outcome of the questionnaire is purely used as a conversation starter. During the second interview, we focus on your drivers, your ambitions and how you match with the ASML culture. This interview typically takes place on-site, giving you a chance to meet in person with your interviewers and get a feel of our work environment. [->p<-] If your resume matches the job requirements and your application is selected, you\u2019ll be invited to your first interview at ASML. The interview process will vary depending on the job you\u2019re applying for, as well as the region. The first interview is usually a virtual meeting where we discuss your educational and professional experience, as well as your motivation for applying. [->p<-] If the interviews are successful and both sides are excited, we\u2019re ready to make you a job offer. Depending on the country you are applying in, a pre-employment screening may be part of the hiring process. In case you\u2019re not selected, we\u2019ll provide you with feedback, as soon as possible. [->p<-] Following the interview process, it\u2019s time for both sides to evaluate and decide. After careful consideration, the team will make a decision and notify you as soon as possible. The same goes for you, how did you experience the interviews? Are you excited to join us? [->p<-] Curious about what life at ASML is really like? You now can discover how we work, play and thrive, through an exclusive VR experience full of games and challenges.\u00a0 [->p<-] Take a tour of our Veldhoven campus in the Netherlands and learn more about the employee services our teams enjoy, the sports we love to do, what we like to eat, and where we socialize with other colleagues.\u00a0 [->p<-] Access the experience by simply clicking the link below or by scanning the QR code with your phone. [->p<-] Culture & Values [->p<-] Work/life balance [->p<-] Senior Management [->p<-] Compensation and Benefits [->p<-] Career opportunities [->p<-] Diversity & Inclusion [->p<-] Use the ASML job search to find a position that matches your skill set. Click the \"Apply now\" button on any open job listing at ASML, which will direct you to the ASML career portal. From there, you can fill out the form and submit your application. We are unable to accept job applications submitted any other way, such as via email. [->p<-] A recruitment specialist in the department of the open position will review your resume and cover letter. [->p<-] An ASML recruiter will contact you within two weeks if we have questions about your application or if we would like to schedule an interview. [->p<-] We encourage you to apply as soon as possible, as the job listing expiration date depends on the number of qualified applicants. [->p<-] Yes, but we encourage you to only apply for jobs that match your background and experience. If you are invited for the second round of interviews for both positions, you will need to choose with which position you would like to proceed. [->p<-] After you have filled out the online application for a job at ASML, you will see an option to create a personal profile in the career portal. After creating a profile, you can log in and view the status of your job application. [->p<-] If your application status appears as \"closed\", it means that you were not selected to proceed to the next step of the hiring process. We encourage you to search for a job at ASML that matches your skill set and apply again. [->p<-] Our company\u2019s main language is English. We are proudly culturally diverse, with 120 different nationalities working together as one. [->p<-] ASML organizes several events each year for students and professionals that take place at our various locations around the world.  [->p<-] \u00a0to find an event that matches your interests. [->p<-] Get in touch with your local ASML recruitment department. You can use one of the contact forms on this page. [->p<-] The ASML interview process will vary depending on the job you are applying for as well as which country you are applying in. Generally, however, you may have two or more interviews for a job at ASML. The first interview, which takes place with the position\u2019s hiring manager and a member of the team, assesses your background, skills and compatibility with the team. [->p<-] If you are invited for a second interview, you may be asked to complete an online assessment that should be submitted before the interview takes place. The second interview takes place with a project leader, architect or different team member. You may also be invited to a third interview with the human resources (HR) department. If all interviews are successful, you will then receive a job offer from HR. [->p<-] Our virtual interview scheduling assistant, called Rex, will contact you to set up the interview. Rex will send you an email or text message (WhatsApp or SMS) that includes information about the format of the interview, the location, date, and the interviewers, once the interview details have been arranged. [->p<-] Please contact the recruiter that sent you the interview confirmation. [->p<-] We are committed to an open culture of trust and honest communication, where violations of the [->p<-] are not tolerated. Anyone can [->p<-] with respect to our Code of Conduct through ASML\u2019s global\u00a0 [->p<-] . People who speak up will be protected for raising concerns about suspected misconduct in good faith. Reports will be treated confidentially and parties can report concerns anonymously. [->p<-] Scammers may post fraudulent job openings and contact job seekers with fake job offers. They may even conduct fraudulent interviews and attempt to obtain money or personal information.  [->p<-]  for all the information you need to identify and respond to recruitment fraud. [->p<-] If you are an 'international local hire' \u2013 in other words, you were hired to work in a different country or state than where you currently live \u2013 ASML will support the relocation of you and your direct family members (spouse and children). ASML will provide support for immigration, travel, shipping personal belongings, cultural awareness and language training, and tax advice. [->p<-] If your spouse is a good fit for another ASML vacancy, you can both join the ASML referral program. [->p<-] We support lifelong learning for all employees, individually and collectively, across the globe. We do so by offering an appropriate blend of training, on-the-job learning experience and facilitating meaningful connections and collaboration through all parts and layers of the organization. Together with managers who support and Learning & Development that enables, employees are empowered to continuously drive their own development so as to optimally support our business and customers. Our offering covers development in the area of technical skills development, as well as in the area of soft skills and (personal) leadership development. [->p<-] We believe that we share knowledge, innovate and collaborate best when meeting in person, but we recognize that some tasks can be done just as effectively outside the office. ASML\u2019s work-from-home guidelines blend office and remote working, as we believe both have benefits for individuals, the business and the environment. [->p<-] Working from abroad is generally not permissible due to tax, social security and other implications for both the employee and ASML. [->p<-] We are committed to respecting and protecting the privacy of our candidates. Any personal data we receive is managed in a professional, lawful and ethical way, in line with our Code of Conduct and in compliance with applicable laws and regulations. Please read our  [->p<-] Your data is kept only for the period required for recruitment and compliance purposes. Please read more about how long we keep personal data in our  [->p<-] You will need to contact the Privacy Office to have your personal data deleted. Please read more about this process in our  [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] Explore careers at ASML and join the high-tech semiconductor industry, where you can work on technology that can change the world. [->div<-] Find out what it\u2019s like working at a semiconductor industry leader. Discover job benefits, clubs and events, and our culture. [->div<-] With over 60 locations worldwide, we are a growing global force in the semiconductor industry."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] General recruitment inquiries"]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Interviewing at ASML: Tips and tricks"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] ASML's Glassdoor rating [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] The application process [->h3<-] The interview process [->h3<-] Tips from our recruiters [->h3<-] Hop on a virtual reality tour of life at ASML [->h3<-] Careers FAQ and contact [->h3<-] Careers [->h3<-] Working at ASML [->h3<-] ASML at a glance"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Read our most frequently asked questions about interviewing with ASML. [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] At ASML, we value creativity, diversity and fresh ideas, so during the interview stage we encourage you to show up fully as yourself. Applying and interviewing for a new job can be stressful but with the right preparation you can confidently tackle anything. On this page you\u2019ll find useful information about how we conduct interviews and how to best prepare for them. [->h5<-] If you\u2019re looking for your next career challenge, you can browse j [->h5<-]  to discover the right position for you. But before you do that, make sure you consider your skills, your talents and your career aspirations. [->h5<-] Your second interview [->h5<-] Your first interview [->h5<-] Evaluate and decide [->h5<-] Getting an offer [->h5<-] Contact an ASML office [->h5<-] Internship and education inquiries"]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] \u201cDo some research. Prepare questions on the role and its responsibilities beforehand. This will give you a better understanding of the position and shows the interviewers your motivation and interest for the specific job.\u201d [->h6<-] \u201cMake sure to listen carefully to the questions. What is it exactly that the interviewer would like to know? Make sure to answer in a comprehensive and concise way. It\u2019s ok to ask a clarifying question, to take some time before responding, and even to admit that you don\u2019t know something. Authenticity will make you stand out and better connect with the interviewers.\u201d [->h6<-] Read our most\u00a0 [->h6<-] \u00a0or get in touch with the recruitment team at ASML locations."]], ["span", ["[->span<-] Preparing your resume [->span<-] Finding the right vacancy [->span<-] Applying [->span<-] Screening process [->span<-] Tips from our recruiters [->span<-] Search for your future job [->span<-] Unlock our world [->span<-] 4.1 [->span<-] / [->span<-] 2822 [->span<-] \u00a0 [->span<-] ratings [->span<-] Average score of 4.1 out of 2822 ratings [->span<-] 3.8 [->span<-] 3.8 out of 5 [->span<-] 3.7 [->span<-] 3.7 out of 5 [->span<-] 3.4 [->span<-] 3.4 out of 5 [->span<-] 3.9 [->span<-] 3.9 out of 5 [->span<-] 3.8 [->span<-] 3.8 out of 5 [->span<-] 4.2 [->span<-] 4.2 out of 5 [->span<-] Applying for a job at ASML [->span<-] How do I apply for a job at ASML? [->span<-] Who will review my job application? [->span<-] When will I hear back after I apply for a job at ASML [->span<-] Until when can I apply for a job listing that does not have an expiration date? [->span<-] Can I apply for more than one job at ASML? [->span<-] What is the status of my job application? [->span<-] What does it mean if my application status is closed? [->span<-] What is the main language spoken at ASML? [->span<-] Can I visit ASML before I apply for a job? [->span<-] How do I request accessibility accommodations during the application or interview process [->span<-] ASML interview process [->span<-] What is the ASML interview process like? [->span<-] When will I receive an invitation for my interview? [->span<-] I've been asked to complete a talent exploration questionnaire for the job I've applied for.\u00a0 What is it and how much time do I have to complete it? [->span<-] The talent exploration questionnaire is purely used as a conversation starter for your second interview. Once you've received it, we encourage you to complete it as soon as possible, and at least two days before your next interview with ASML [->span<-] When will I hear back after my interview? [->span<-] It depends on the country in which you are applying for a job, but you should generally receive feedback within five working days. [->span<-] \ufeff [->span<-] I did not receive a QR code or online meeting link for my interview. [->span<-] How can I register a complaint about the interview process? [->span<-] How can I identify recruitment fraud? [->span<-] Working at ASML [->span<-] Does ASML offer relocation support? [->span<-] Can you help my spouse in finding a job as well? [->span<-] Does ASML help with continued learning and development? [->span<-] Does ASML offer remote jobs? [->span<-] Privacy [->span<-] How does ASML use my personal data? [->span<-] How long will ASML keep my personal data? [->span<-] How can I request that my personal data be deleted? [->span<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Related Content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Be part of progress. Join a dynamic, global collaboration pushing semiconductor technology to new limits to improve the way we live, work and play [->p<-] At ASML, we create groundbreaking technology to solve some of society's toughest challenges. But all this innovation doesn't just happen. It's the grit, passion and dedication of our people that allows us to push technology to new limits every day. At ASML, you're welcome to be fully yourself as we support you in reaching your full potential. [->p<-] We\u2019re a diverse team of tech experts, connected by our  [->p<-] . Together, we challenge, collaborate and care. Read on to find out how each of our values is reflected in our work and life at ASML. [->p<-] Working at the cutting edge of tech, you\u2019ll always have new challenges and new problems to solve. Our industry ecosystem is constantly evolving and innovating, and you will too. But the work isn\u2019t just challenging and exciting, it\u2019s rewarding. Your contributions will profoundly impact society, because\u00a0\u2013\u00a0from smartphones to automotive tech\u00a0\u2013\u00a0if it\u2019s moving the world forward, we\u2019re behind it. [->p<-] Working together is the only way to solve the complex, intriguing problems you and your team will face daily. So you won\u2019t work in a silo. Instead, you'll thrive in a creative, dynamic work environment where you\u2019ll collaborate with supportive colleagues. [->p<-] We are proud to say that ASML is an environment of mutual respect, where people feel valued \u2013 an environment that leads to better results than any of us could achieve alone. You will have the flexibility and trust to choose how best to tackle tasks and solve problems. And, because we champion a diverse and inclusive workforce, there is always space for creative and unique points of view. [->p<-] STORIES [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Meet Manisha Devi, who spearheaded the rollout of a new digital platform under pressure [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Meet Ron Kool, who made a bold career transition to improve ASML\u2019s business processes [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Faced with a complex issue, Anya Kish rose to the challenge by turning it into a growth opportunity [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Meet Mark Bergkotte, who believes focusing on employees\u2019 health and well-being is the key to success [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] From accounting to relationship building, Manon Hendriks\u2019s career is full of growth and inspiration [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Meet George Tao, who turns time constraints into team triumphs [->p<-] Discover how ASML fosters a culture of innovation through on-the-job training, top learning and development solutions and personalized knowledge programs.\u00a0 [->p<-] Wondering what our work culture is like? Dive into this interactive section and\u00a0discover what it\u2019s like to be an ASML employee.\u00a0 [->p<-] It\u2019s important to us that you stay healthy, happy and energetic \u2013 and make the most of your career at ASML. Through this program, we will support you to foster your own well-being and positive work-life balance through courses, great working environments, flexibility and more. [->p<-] Being part of ASML means being part of something bigger than yourself. We play an active role in the communities we operate in, and you can too. You\u2019ll be able to volunteer, give back to your community and make a difference. [->p<-] Are you interested in sustainability? A keen sportsperson? Passionate \u2013 like us \u2013 about diversity and inclusion? When you work at ASML there are lots of opportunities to get involved and build professional connections as well as friendships. Find out about our networks and clubs for ASML employees. [->p<-] Did you know that we annually host one of the largest developer events in the world? From holiday-inspired occasions to community and industry events, there\u2019s always another occasion on our calendar that you can join. [->p<-] Consider your career path a playground. We have various tools in place to support you in driving your own development, from classroom training to personal coaching, potential acceleration programs and more. Learn how, with ASML, you\u2019ll have the time, opportunity, and support to drive your own development. [->p<-] We want you to join ASML to be part of progress. And we want you to stay because you share in our success. We offer highly competitive compensation and benefits packages to attract and retain the very best talent, which means your package will cover much more than just a salary. [->p<-] ASML\u2019s success is driven by our unique and diverse teams. United by our passion for technology, we draw on our core values of challenge, collaborate and care to foster a safe, inclusive environment where everyone is empowered to contribute. [->p<-] Work at asml [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] We support both global big-name customers and fast-growing local customers with 12 customer support sites, two R&D centers, and one training center. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Japan is home to tech giants and major semiconductor players, with whom ASML collaborates closely. You can help to advance technology \u2013 and your career. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] ASML is headquartered in Veldhoven amid a thriving ecosystem of high-tech companies. Our headquarters is home to more than half of all our employees. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Our teams in South Korea work closely with Samsung and other customers and have five locations that include a global distribution center and 4 training centers. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] We have the largest ASML manufacturing site in Asia as well as two training centers, play an essential role in the rapidly growing e-beam market, and work closely with TSMC and major semiconductor fabs. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] With 14 customer support sites, two factories, and three R&D centers, our US locations service Intel and other customers and contribute to our holistic product portfolio. [->p<-] Visit our interview tips page to learn more about ASML\u2019s job application and interview process. [->p<-] Culture & Values [->p<-] Work/life balance [->p<-] Senior Management [->p<-] Compensation and Benefits [->p<-] Career opportunities [->p<-] Diversity & Inclusion"]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] Our Germany locations, such as Berlin and Dresden, specialize in optical manufacturing technology, precision manufacturing, as well as software development and customer support. [->div<-] Explore job opportunities by technical fields, ranging from data science to mechatronics and everything in between. [->div<-] See our internships, scholarships, and career events for students and graduates in the Netherlands and the US. [->div<-] R&D, manufacturing, and customer support are the pillars of our organization, supported by our corporate functions."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] "]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Working at ASML"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] ASML's Glassdoor rating [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] What\u2019s it like working for a semiconductor industry leader? [->h3<-] 7 practical ways you can grow and develop at ASML\u00a0 [->h3<-] Technical fields [->h3<-] Students & new graduates [->h3<-] Organization"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Challenging work that is changing the world [->h4<-] Collaboration is the key [->h4<-] Care and respect for all [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] "]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 41 [->span<-] Search for your future job [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] People of ASML [->span<-] Delivering for our customers [->span<-] Embracing change, driving innovation [->span<-] Making a difference [->span<-] Helping our teams thrive\u00a0\u00a0 [->span<-] Working together, growing together [->span<-] Impact through collaboration [->span<-] Read the story [->span<-] Discover life at ASML [->span<-] Well-being [->span<-] Purpose [->span<-] Networks and clubs [->span<-] Events [->span<-] Learning & development [->span<-] Benefits [->span<-] Diversity & inclusion [->span<-] 60 locations, endless job opportunities [->span<-] Chinese mainland [->span<-] Germany [->span<-] Japan [->span<-] The Netherlands [->span<-] South Korea [->span<-] Taiwan [->span<-] United States [->span<-] Questions about job applications? [->span<-] 4.1 [->span<-] / [->span<-] 2822 [->span<-] \u00a0 [->span<-] ratings [->span<-] Average score of 4.1 out of 2822 ratings [->span<-] 3.8 [->span<-] 3.8 out of 5 [->span<-] 3.7 [->span<-] 3.7 out of 5 [->span<-] 3.4 [->span<-] 3.4 out of 5 [->span<-] 3.9 [->span<-] 3.9 out of 5 [->span<-] 3.8 [->span<-] 3.8 out of 5 [->span<-] 4.2 [->span<-] 4.2 out of 5 [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] We\u2019re an international company with Dutch roots. See what we do in the Netherlands and what it\u2019s like working there. [->p<-] Employees [->p<-] Buildings [->p<-] Nationalities [->p<-] Hours spent volunteering by employees in 2025 [->p<-] Tulips, windmills and wooden shoes aren\u2019t the only things that the Netherlands is famous for. ASML is helping to put the Netherlands on the map as a high-tech hub.\u00a0 [->p<-] Our headquarters is in Veldhoven in the Brainport Eindhoven region. This fast-growing region offers high living standards, a culture that embraces a healthy work-life balance, and exciting opportunities for professional development.\u00a0 [->p<-] - Hajo Lotgerink, DUV learning architect [->p<-] Differences based on salary grade may apply [->p<-] We understand what it\u2019s like moving to a new country. We offer help with relocation, which includes temporary housing, moving services for furniture and other belongings, and a relocation budget for the various costs associated with the move. [->p<-] The Holland Expat Center South can help you and your family to settle into your new living and working environment. [->p<-] Curious about what life at ASML is really like? You now can discover how we work, play and thrive, through an exclusive VR experience full of games and challenges.\u00a0\u00a0 [->p<-] Take a tour of our Veldhoven campus in the Netherlands and learn more about the employee services our teams enjoy, the sports we love to do, what we like to eat, and where we socialize with other colleagues.\u00a0\u00a0 [->p<-] Access the experience by simply clicking the link below or by scanning the QR code with your phone.\u00a0  [->p<-] life at asml [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Learn how we will support you to foster your own well-being and work-life balance, through courses, great working environment, flexibility and more. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Being part of ASML means being part of something bigger that yourself. Discover the many ways you'll be able to volunteer, give back to your community and make a difference. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Are you interested in sustainability? A keen sportsperson? Passionate - like us - about diversity and inclusion? Find out about our network and clubs for ASML employees. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Did you know that we annually host one of the largest developer events in the world? From holiday-inspired occasions to community and industry events, there\u2019s always another occasion on our calendar that you can join. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Consider your career path a playground. We have various tools in place to support you in driving your own development, from classroom training to personal coaching, potential acceleration programs and more. Learn how, with ASML, you\u2019ll have the time, opportunity, and support to drive your own development. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] We want you to join ASML to be part of progress. And we want you to stay because you share in our success. We offer highly competitive compensation and benefits packages to attract and retain the very best talent, which means your package will cover much more than just a salary. [->p<-] Pre-employment screening is one of the final steps in the selection process for both jobs and internships in the Netherlands. This takes place after the candidate has accepted the offer and agreed to begin the screening process. Pre-employment screening ensures we meet legal obligations and protect ASML assets as well as its employees and contractors. [->p<-] As part of the screening process, we will check information related to identity and education as provided by the candidate, public or government-released sanction lists, and social media sources. For certain vacancies in the Finance, Procurement, IT, Sales, Security and Airfreight sectors, additional checks regarding the resume, references, criminal record and credit risk may be performed. [->p<-] Fill in the form below to get in touch with the ASML recruitment department for the Netherlands. We\u2019ll get back to you as soon as possible! [->p<-] Your privacy matters to ASML and we comply with applicable data protection laws. Please read the\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0carefully before submitting this form."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] k [->div<-] + [->div<-] K [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] ( [->div<-] Optional [->div<-] ) [->div<-] With over 60 locations worldwide, we are a growing global force in the semiconductor industry. [->div<-] Three continents, 16 countries and regions, 60 locations. Find out more about what it\u2019s like working at a world leader in the semiconductor industry. [->div<-] Discover ASML at our student excursions, career day, business course, job fairs and university lunch lectures."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] Competitive salary [->li<-] 13th month payment [->li<-] 8% holiday allowance [->li<-] 40 days paid leave: 27 vacation days and 13 ADV days (reduction of working hours) [->li<-] Variable pay [->li<-] Employee share purchase plan [->li<-] Pension plan [->li<-] Collective health insurance plan [->li<-] Commuting allowance [->li<-] Reimbursement for relocation expenses [->li<-] Training and development opportunities, including educational assistance through our Global Training and Studies program"]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] "]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] Working in the Netherlands"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] The Netherlands at a glance [->h3<-] Hop on a virtual reality tour of our Veldhoven campus! [->h3<-] ASML at a glance [->h3<-] Locations [->h3<-] Career events in the Netherlands"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Our headquarters is in Veldhoven. We also have locations in nearby Eindhoven and Oirschot, and further north in Delft. The Netherlands is where most of our R&D and operations are based, and it is home to more than half of all ASML employees. [->h4<-] ASML compensation and benefits in the Netherlands [->h4<-] Read our most frequently asked questions about applying for a job at ASML in the Netherlands. [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] "]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] 0 [->span<-] 1 [->span<-] 2 [->span<-] 3 [->span<-] 4 [->span<-] 5 [->span<-] 6 [->span<-] 7 [->span<-] 8 [->span<-] 9 [->span<-] Unlock our world [->span<-] Explore all topics [->span<-] Well being [->span<-] Purpose [->span<-] Networks and clubs [->span<-] Events [->span<-] Learn and develop [->span<-] Benefits [->span<-] Where is ASML located in the Netherlands? [->span<-] The ASML headquarters is in Veldhoven. Close by in Oirschot, our teams focus on stage motor design and assembly. Further north, in Delft, our teams focus on metrology and inspection solutions. [->span<-] What is working at ASML in the Netherlands like? [->span<-] Learn more about\u00a0 [->span<-] \u00a0including our culture and values as well as employee benefits. One of the best ways to get to know ASML is by attending a\u00a0 [->span<-] , which may include campus tours and Q&A sessions with real ASML employees. [->span<-] Can you help find my spouse a job in the Netherlands? [->span<-] ASML does offer relocation support, but no direct job-seeking support for spouses of ASML employees. Your spouse can join the\u00a0 [->span<-] \u00a0for help to find their way in the job market and set up their network in the region. [->span<-] What is pre-employment screening? [->span<-] Where can I find more more information about applying for a job, the interview process and what it\u2019s like to work at ASML? [->span<-] Read our  [->span<-] interview tips [->span<-]  to learn more about ASML\u2019s job application and interview process. [->span<-] Contact us [->span<-] Enable third party cookies to view this form [->span<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Your message [->span<-] Related content [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] With 14 customer support sites, two factories and three R&D centers, ASML in the US is an important development and manufacturing hub serving global chipmakers such as Intel [->p<-] Employees [->p<-] Customer support centers [->p<-] Manufacturing factories [->p<-] R&D sites [->p<-] Click to see our main hubs in the US [->p<-] Chandler, Arizona [->p<-] Hillsboro, Oregon [->p<-] San Diego, California [->p<-] Silicon Valley, California [->p<-] Wilton, Connecticut [->p<-] Home to our US Global Support Center for customers, our Chandler office houses employees from Customer Support, sales, and other support departments. [->p<-] Our largest US customer support site, responsible for delivering the highest level of service throughout the life cycle of a lithography system. It\u2019s also the main training hub for customer support engineers in the US. [->p<-] The epicenter for the development and manufacturing of EUV light sources for lithography systems. It's also the main office of Cymer, an independently operated DUV light source business within ASML. [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Our software and R&D powerhouse, specializing in computational applications to help chipmakers achieve higher manufacturing yields, as well as e-beam metrology technology expertise. [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Our largest US office and second-largest R&D center in ASML, with expertise in mechatronics, alignment and sensor technology and world-class optical R&D and manufacturing abilities. [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Find out what it\u2019s like working as a computer scientist or software developer at ASML working in C++, C#, Python or Java. [->p<-] Design, build and test exceptionally high-performance systems as a mechanical engineer at ASML. [->p<-] Work at the leading edge of electrical innovation. Explore the opportunities for electrical engineers at ASML. [->p<-] If you enjoy working at or beyond the edge of what\u2019s possible in optics, then ASML is your ideal environment. [->p<-] Physics is at the heart of everything we do at ASML. Explore our opportunities for physicists. [->p<-] Design and build some of the most advanced electron-beam measurement tools in the semiconductor industry. [->p<-] No two days are alike in this fast-paced, precision cleanroom environment. [->p<-] Discover jobs in sourcing & procurement and start planning for your future. [->p<-] Work around the clock to make sure the world\u2019s most advanced chipmaking machines run smoothly. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] A completely magnetically levitated stage accelerates at more than 15 g, more than three times the g-force experienced by a fighter jet pilot at takeoff, up to a constant velocity of more than three meters per second. It positions the chipmaker\u2019s reticle (blueprint of the chip pattern) within fractions of nanometers in all six degrees of freedom at full speed. [->p<-] The droplet generator is the heartbeat of the EUV light source, delivering a steady stream of 50,000 liquid tin droplets per second, which fly at more than 241 kilometers per hour in a vacuum vessel. Each droplet \u2013 whose size is a fraction of the thickness of a human hair \u2013 is individually imaged and targeted by two high-power CO2 laser pulses, generating a plasma that emits EUV light. [->p<-] Today\u2019s chips have billions of transistors, built up layer by layer with extreme precision, requiring the imaging of tens of billions of patterns that must be simulated and optimized within 24 hours \u2013 it\u2019s an enormous, time-sensitive task. We harness the power of tens of thousands of computing cores to quickly process full chip blueprints \u2013 all without sacrificing accuracy. [->p<-] Our Proud network supports LGBTIQ+ rights and inclusion around the world, welcoming a wide gender spectrum and expression. You aren\u2019t just included at ASML \u2013 you belong here. [->p<-] SHADES is cultivating a network and resources to drive the advancement of BIPOC, international, and multicultural employees, and relies on allyship to help promote diversity and inclusion at ASML. [->p<-] Women and WAVES are networks creating a strong, connected group of women and supportive colleagues, with the goal to see an increasing balance in leadership roles. [->p<-] Atypical, ASML\u2019s neurodiversity employee network, is helping to raise awareness about brain differences and how normal they really are. [->p<-] The Green network at ASML focuses on reducing and reversing the environmental impact of both our company and individual employees. [->p<-] Military veterans possess valuable experience and skills that are in high demand at ASML. Our Veterans employee network provides outreach to veterans and their families. [->p<-] Next\u2019s goal is to engage, connect and grow the 'next generation' at ASML. Next is a thriving community of professionals who share ideas and network with colleagues from diverse backgrounds. [->p<-] The Parents network is a great place to connect with fellow ASML parents, support one another [->p<-] and share practical information, and promote family-friendly policies. [->p<-] Meet Alanna Mohammed, Quality Control Inspector [->p<-] Meet Eileen Behrendt, Electrical Sensors & Illumination [->p<-] Meet John Hilliker, Mechanical Engineering Group Lead [->p<-] Meet Mike Mercer, Optical Technician [->p<-] Meet Piyush Savlani, Electrical Engineering Group Lead [->p<-] Meet Ricardo Duran-Rodriguez, Software Engineer [->p<-] Meet Shubhangi Alande, Software Engineer [->p<-] Meet Yu Gong, Senior Optical Sensing Engineer [->p<-] Find out what it\u2019s like working in our optics team in Wilton, Connecticut, and learn how you can pursue your education through our tuition reimbursement program. [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Hear about Eileen\u2019s experience at ASML over the last eight years and the different techniques we use to build our machines. [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Take a deep dive into ASML\u2019s culture and learn how we support each other daily to produce creative solutions. [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Hear about how Mike was able to shift gears from the military to a career in ASML\u2019s Wilton Factory in Connecticut. [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Learn more about how chipmakers use ASML\u2019s machines to print circuits on silicon wafers. [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Discover how ASML\u2019s San Diego software team works on the lasers in our lithography machines. [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Learn more about how ASML\u2019s machines power the next generation of technology and get a glimpse of our software development. [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Learn more about how ASML\u2019s scanning electron microscope (the SEM) team fits into the creation of our machines and how we navigates the nano world. [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Family and health benefits, incentive plans and up to 38 days\u2019 paid time off. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] \u201cInternal mobility is embedded in ASML\u2019s culture. I simply would not have developed as I have in the same time frame without seeing the business from different angles.\u201d\u00a0 [->p<-] \u201cCareer development is a true priority here, with continuous learning and growth encouraged at every stage. Anything is possible!\u201d\u00a0 [->p<-] \u201cTraining programs are important, but we also recognize that on-the-job learning is where the majority of skill development takes place.\u201d\u00a0 [->p<-] \u201cI\u2019ve participated in quite a few leadership training programs throughout my ASML career that have helped me immensely.\u201d\u00a0 [->p<-] Be the first to know about job openings, read employee stories, and get the latest ASML news in our monthly talent community newsletter."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] k [->div<-] + [->div<-] Learn more about ASML at our campus events and conferences in the US. [->div<-] R&D, manufacturing, and customer support are the pillars of our organization, supported by our corporate functions. [->div<-] From a leaky wooden shed to a global force, ASML's journey in the semiconductor industry began in 1984."]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] 85% average employer-paid medical and dental benefits, with a range of options for employees and their eligible dependents [->li<-] 100% employer-paid vision benefits, basic life insurance [->li<-] Annual short-term plan for all employees [->li<-] Long-term stock plan available for eligible employees [->li<-] \u00a020% employer-paid premium available after first year of participation\u00a0 [->li<-] ASML will match 100% on the first 3% eligible compensation deferred, plus 2% of eligible compensation deferred, for a maximum employer match of 4% per plan year with immediate vesting. [->li<-] Paid time off: Up to 38 days of leave per year (vacation and holidays) scaled based on tenure [->li<-] A flexible workplace policy supporting work-life balance [->li<-] Onsite and virtual well-being services and offerings [->li<-] Mental health and well-being counseling and resources [->li<-] Holistic well-being \u2018challenges\u2019 [->li<-] Calm mindfulness app [->li<-] Cash out unused vacation time [->li<-] Paid parental leave [->li<-] Adoption assistance (up to $10,000) [->li<-] Milk shipment for new mothers required to travel [->li<-] IVF Coverage (up to $20,000 lifetime) [->li<-] Peer-to-peer thank you program (gift cards) [->li<-] Awards of scaled value granted to employees who reach milestones (beginning at three years) [->li<-] Employee Assistance Program available to emplo