rty cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Customer support engineers are responsible for supporting the installation, upgrade, relocation, and maintenance of ASML lithography systems at customer sites. They provide first-line technical support for ASML systems, monitor system performance and operations, and help identify and resolve equipment issues.\u00a0 [->p<-] Technical support engineers provide advanced technical expertise for specific modules and systems. They analyze complex technical issues, support performance optimization, and deliver solutions for both internal teams and customers. They play a critical role in driving continuous improvements in system performance and reliability.\u00a0 [->p<-] Field application engineers work closely with customers to optimize lithography performance and improve wafer process results. By leveraging data analysis and technical expertise, they identify solutions for complex challenges and collaborate with customers to enhance productivity and manufacturing efficiency. [->p<-] life at asml [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Learn how we will support you to foster your own well-being and work-life balance, through courses, great working environment, flexibility and more. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Being part of ASML means being part of something bigger that yourself. Discover the many ways you'll be able to volunteer, give back to your community and make a difference. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Are you interested in sustainability? A keen sportsperson? Passionate - like us - about diversity and inclusion? Find out about our network and clubs for ASML employees. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Did you know that we annually host one of the largest developer events in the world? From holiday-inspired occasions to community and industry events, there\u2019s always another occasion on our calendar that you can join. [->p<-] Read more [->p<-] Consider your career path a playground. We have various tools in place to s