hts Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] How ASML is applying AI-native engineering for the next technology era\u00a0 [->p<-] June 12, 2026 [->p<-] In a keynote, Arnaud Hubaux, Head of AI Program & Strategy, shared how ASML is applying AI across our products and operations to accelerate design cycles, improve system performance, enhance defect detection and reduce service time. \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] The event also reflects our growing  [->p<-] , a partner helping us apply advanced AI models and agents to complex engineering and operational challenges. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] When people think about AI, they often see models, applications and user experiences. What remains largely unseen is the physical infrastructure that makes it possible. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] At the center of that infrastructure are AI chips \u2013 highly specialized microprocessors designed to handle the massive, parallel computations required for machine learning. As the leading supplier of holistic lithography solutions used to manufacture these chips, ASML plays a pivotal role in the AI revolution. \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] \u201cEvery time AI does something that feels unreal, it is not magic,\u201d Arnaud said during his keynote. \u201cIt is matter. It is physics. It is human precision.\u201d [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] ASML has been applying AI in targeted hardware and software solutions for more than a decade. Today, this approach is shifting. Instead of using AI as point solutions, we are integrating it across workflows and systems. \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] This shift allows us to apply AI consistently across the semiconductor life cycle \u2013 helping our teams accelerate the realization of new engineering innovation while improving the performance and reliability of our systems. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] One way we\u2019re enabling this transformation is through our partnership with Mistral AI. \u201cMistral AI\u2019s expertise in models and agents complements our knowledge of physics, engineering and real-world system behavior,\u201d says Arnaud. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Embedding AI across the semiconductor life cycle starts at the chip design phase. AI helps bridge the gap between intent and final result by improving the many steps required to make a chip design manufacturable. \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] The first step is optical proximity correction (OPC), which modifies the reticle design to meet imaging targets by compensating for distortions that occur during production. ASML has used AI in OPC for more than a decade to accelerate computation. Now, together with Mistral AI, we are improving recipe quality and accelerating time to solution. In January 2026, we completed early validation of our first generative AI capability with a customer.\u00a0 [->p<-] Inside our machines, AI helps optimize and control highly complex physical processes. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Let\u2019s start at the source \u2013 literally. ASML\u2019s  [->p<-]  light source sits at the heart of the lithography system, turning the output of an extremely powerful laser into the EUV light needed to achieve the precision required by most advanced chips.\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] AI helps us to optimize and calibrate EUV source settings \u2013 reducing manual trial-and-error and enabling faster, more robust system initialization. Early tests have delivered increased wafer-level power gain in EUV scanners at a customer. \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Being able to inspect what lithography machines print is critical to maintaining yield, but high-resolution analysis can limit throughput. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] AI helps solve this trade-off. By enhancing image quality and guiding where and how to inspect, we are able to increase the throughput of our electron-beam (e-beam) metrology and inspection systems \u2013 while maintaining accuracy and reliability. This is another area where ASML and Mistral are working together. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] In the field, system uptime is critical, but diagnosing issues in systems that generate terabytes of data is increasingly complex. AI helps process unstructured data such as error logs and service records to identify root causes more quickly. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] In early pilots with Mistral AI, AI-driven diagnostics have identified certain sub-system errors more than 70% faster while matching engineers\u2019 accuracy. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] \u201cData only creates value if you can use it,\u201d Arnaud says. \u201cAI helps make that knowledge accessible across the organization.\u201d [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] AI is also helping us accelerate design cycles and improve components. It enables engineers to explore more design alternatives in high-dimensional problem spaces while accounting for real-world constraints such as cost and manufacturability. So far, more than 12,000 designs have been explored. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] \u201cAI is there to augment our engineers, not replace them,\u201d Arnaud says. \u201cThe future is expert teams amplified by intelligent systems.\u201d [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] At ASML, engineering expertise remains the foundation. Engineers define problems, understand system behavior and validate outcomes in real-world conditions. AI accelerates this work. It helps teams iterate faster, handle more complexity and troubleshoot more effectively. Over time, this creates a continuous learning loop: engineers define and build, AI accelerates design and optimization, systems generate data, and that data improves the AI. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] AI demand is growing rapidly worldwide, putting increasing pressure on lithography systems to deliver higher performance while managing rising complexity. Traditional approaches alone are no longer sufficient. In this emerging environment, AI is becoming essential to scaling the next generation of semiconductor technology. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] \u201cASML is positioned at the very beginning and very end of the AI cycle,\u201d Arnaud concludes. \u201cWe\u2019ve been enabling the AI industry with new chips that bring lower cost per token for decades. Now ASML is using AI to accelerate the engineering and delivery of the very systems that enable the AI evolution.\u201d [->p<-] October 04, 2023 [->p<-] February 28, 2024 [->p<-] May 12, 2026"]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] Share this article"]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] 4-minute read - "]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] The machines behind the machines"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] AI Now Summit keynote recording [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Controlling systems at the limits of physics [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] "]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] What sits behind AI [->h4<-] AI across the semiconductor life cycle [->h4<-] Translating chip design into reality [->h4<-] Improving defect detection without slowing speed [->h4<-] Diagnosing issues faster with AI [->h4<-] Designing better systems faster [->h4<-] Engineers and AI: a continuous loop [->h4<-] Why this matters now [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] "]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] Table of contents"]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 43 [->span<-] AI Now Summit keynote recording [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Related Stories [->span<-] 6 crucial steps in semiconductor manufacturing [->span<-] Byte-sized engineering: Why ASML software is a core part of chipmaking [->span<-] Introducing Marco Pieters, ASML\u2019s new CTO\u00a0 [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Powering technology forward with you [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] All figures based on US GAAP [->p<-] More profitability KPIs: [->p<-] Our portfolio-wide innovations tackle the most complex challenges in semiconductor manufacturing, aiming to keep us ahead of market demands and customer expectations.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Our annual customer satisfaction survey measures loyalty and trust, and identifies areas for improvement. [->p<-] 2025 target: Greenhouse gas (GHG) neutral\u00a0 [->p<-] We have reduced our scope 1 and 2 emissions by 60% since 2019 \u2013 and, in 2025, residual emissions of 26 kt have been compensated for to reach our GHG neutrality target. [->p<-] 2040 target: Greenhouse gas (GHG) neutral [->p<-] Our scope 3 emission intensity was 0.67 kt CO [->p<-] e per \u20ac million gross profit \u2013 a reduction against our 2019 base year of 1.44 kt and achieving our SBTi target of 0.93 kt for 2025.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 [->p<-] 2025 target: Reuse rate of 90%\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 [->p<-] Gender diversity: [->p<-] 2025 target: \u20ac2,500 per employee [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Below you can enable third party cookies. Your choice will be saved and the page will refresh. [->p<-] Carousel with 4 items [->p<-] Item 1 [->p<-] Item 2 [->p<-] Item 3 [->p<-] Item 4"]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-]   [->div<-]   [->div<-]   [->div<-]   [->div<-]   [->div<-]   [->div<-] Total net sales\u00a0 [->div<-] \u20ac32.7bn [->div<-] Gross margin\u00a0 [->div<-] 52.8% [->div<-] Research and development [->div<-] \u20ac4.7bn [->div<-] System sales in units [->div<-] 535 [->div<-] Customer satisfaction survey score\u00a0 [->div<-] 88% [->div<-] Total number of suppliers\u00a0\u00a0 [->div<-] 5,100 [->div<-] Net scope 1 and 2 CO\u2082e emissions\u00a0 [->div<-] 0 kt [->div<-] Net scope 3 CO\u2082e emissions [->div<-] 11.5 Mt [->div<-] Reuse rate of parts returned from field and factory [->div<-] 90% [->div<-] Total employees [->div<-] >44,000 [->div<-] FTEs [->div<-] Women in our workforce [->div<-] 21% [->div<-] Headcount [->div<-] Amount invested in communities (per employee), including employee giving\u00a0 [->div<-] \u20ac1,750 [->div<-] Returned to shareholders [->div<-] \u20ac8.5bn"]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] \u20ac28.1bn [->td<-] Asia [->td<-] \u20ac4.1bn [->td<-] United States [->td<-] \u20ac0.5bn [->td<-] EMEA [->td<-] \u20ac17.3bn [->td<-] Gross profit [->td<-] \u20ac11.3bn [->td<-] Income from operations [->td<-] \u20ac9.6bn [->td<-] Net income [->td<-] \u20ac24.73 [->td<-] Earnings per share (basic) [->td<-] 48 [->td<-] EUV lithography systems [->td<-] 279 [->td<-] DUV lithography systems [->td<-] 208 [->td<-] Metrology and inspection systems [->td<-] 1,600 [->td<-] Netherlands [->td<-] 700 [->td<-] EMEA (excl. NL) [->td<-] 1,350 [->td<-] North America [->td<-] 1,450 [->td<-] Asia [->td<-] 60+ [->td<-] Locations [->td<-] 3 [->td<-] Continents [->td<-] 143 [->td<-] Nationalities [->td<-] 29% [->td<-] Inflow of women (all job grades) [->td<-] 28% [->td<-] Inflow of women to job grade 9+ [->td<-] 16% [->td<-] Representation of women in job grade 13+ [->td<-] \u20ac2.6bn [->td<-] Dividends paid [->td<-] \u20ac5.9bn [->td<-] Share buybacks"]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] "]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] "]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] 2025 Annual Report"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Powering technology forward with you [->h2<-] First full-specification TWINSCAN EXE:5200B system delivered to a customer\u00a0\u00a0 [->h2<-] TWINSCAN NXE:3800E \u2013 full-specification system improves throughput by 37%\u00a0\u00a0 [->h2<-] TWINSCAN XT:260 system combines high throughput with imaging accuracy to support 3D integration\u00a0\u00a0 [->h2<-] YieldStar 1390 increases throughput, delivering cost-effective after-etch overlay control\u00a0\u00a0 [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] "]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Our highlights from 2025 [->h4<-] Our holistic approach to lithography\u00a0 [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] "]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] ASML is a leading innovator in the global semiconductor ecosystem. Our hardware, software and services help chipmakers create more powerful, affordable and energy-efficient microchips. [->h6<-] We deliver value throughout the semiconductor value chain. Our comprehensive lithography portfolio enables cost-effective microchip scaling for our customers.\u00a0"]], ["span", ["[->span<-] 01 / 46 [->span<-] Pause video [->span<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Back [->span<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Product highlights [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] Read more [->span<-] More details in the 2025 Annual Report [->span<-] View report [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Saved jobs [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] Back [->p<-] A glimpse of our work culture and what you\u2019ll discover as part of our team, from well-being to development and more [->p<-] ASML plays an active role in the communities we operate in [->p<-] Volunteering is good for business and it feels good too. That's why all ASML employees are encouraged and able to take eight working hours each year to lend a hand as a volunteer. Some of our employees volunteer with programs that the ASML Foundation supports. Employees foster rewarding positive community ties through volunteering, and many also volunteer in their own time. [->p<-] Here's a glimpse of how you can contribute at ASML. [->p<-] A network of ASML volunteers support school-aged children, either as part-time (\u2018hybrid\u2019) teachers, as tutors of disadvantaged children, or as technology and STEM promoters. Employees also volunteer as technology ambassadors, giving lectures in educational settings or hosting students who visit ASML campuses. Other employees help older people boost their digital confidence as part of\u00a0 [->p<-] . [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] \u201cI immediately loved the idea of tutoring underprivileged children and wanted to join, I think I was the first person to sign up! What the children need most is to build confidence through feedback, and hear if they are doing something right or wrong. Most of the parents cannot give that. Over time, I can see their self-confidence growing, which gives me energy.\u201d [->p<-] For example, we partner with the Van Gogh Museum in Amsterdam and Van Gogh Brabant. ASML engineers involved in this partnership are sharing their expertise to help restore and  [->p<-] . [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] We support initiatives and organizations that are vital for the community\u2019s culture and help make them accessible to everyone. [->p<-] \u201cIt\u2019s a diverse partnership with many institutions involved, which makes it exciting and fun. I\u2019m fascinated by the commonalities and differences between making tools and techniques for making semiconductor chips, and how these can be used for conserving art and art pieces. That\u2019s exciting.\u201d [->p<-] Our local outreach activities include collecting winter coats for people in need, distributing Christmas presents for children from financially disadvantaged families and supporting an online vitality program for the Brainport Eindhoven community. [->p<-] We aim to have a positive influence in the communities in which we operate. Through our volunteers supported by ASML, we\u2019re focused on strengthening local communities by supporting local initiatives. [->p<-] For ASML employees in eligible countries, we match their donations to nonprofit organizations euro-to-euro up to a cumulative amount of \u20ac10,000 per employee, per calendar year. [->p<-] To nurture innovation in new generations, we foster entrepreneurship in local technical talent, helping young enterprises to excel and grow. Experts from within ASML mentor and share their in-depth competencies and knowledge with startups and scaleups. [->p<-] We have never forgotten that it\u2019s our startup mentality \u2013 innovative, adaptable, purpose driven \u2013 that has helped us grow to be an industry leader. We also haven\u2019t forgotten that the startup phase can be hard. [->p<-] Robotics soccer teams, groups for young and old, and everything in between \u2013 ASML networks and clubs offer something for everyone [->p<-] Our employee-led networks and clubs foster a supportive environment and enhance a sense of belonging in our workplace. [->p<-] Around the world we have various networks and clubs tailored to local interests. These groups each have a collective theme, but are open to all \u2013 whether you identify personally with the theme or are simply interested to learn more or to support the group\u2019s efforts. [->p<-] Below you\u2019ll find an overview of some of our popular groups. [->p<-] The Green network at ASML focuses on reducing and reversing the environmental impact of both our company and individual employees. Through regular events and newsletters, our employees are promoting sustainability leadership and responsibility. [->p<-] As part of\u00a0 [->p<-] , you can join a project or start your own initiative. Existing activities include global clean-up days and monthly talks from professionals. Other green initiatives include a switch to compostable coffee machine cups, and a flight CO2\u00a0compensation program. With support from Green, you can even identify and measure how your personal performance can contribute to ASML\u2019s sustainability targets. [->p<-] \u201cGreen was formed by people with a shared mindset to take action on improving our company\u2019s sustainability. It\u2019s great to meet people from all over ASML, learn about what they do regarding sustainability and collaborate with them. I get to see the energy that our colleagues have to challenge our operations daily, and to work with so many people that are enthusiastic about sustainability and driven to improve ASML in this aspect.\u201d [->p<-] We have several networks for people in different stages of their life to connect with each other. Whether you are at the start of your career or nearing retirement, you\u2019ll find a group where you can share knowledge and keep developing yourself. The best part is that these groups are not age-specific \u2013 no matter your age, you are welcome to join! [->p<-] is a thriving community of professionals who share ideas and network with colleagues from diverse backgrounds. As a member, you can join, lead and contribute to initiatives such as management lunches, lectures, workshops and trainings. [->p<-] is a group that supports colleagues throughout their career, and shares knowledge through mentorship, informal gatherings and events. [->p<-] \u201cSeniors doesn\u2019t stand for \u2018old\u2019 or \u2018management\u2019, but for \u2018experienced\u2019. Our network focuses on work-life balance, sustainable employability and preparation for the next stages of life. I enjoy organizing lectures on these topics.\u201d [->p<-] \u201cThrough Next, I\u2019ve learned to find my way in our growing organization. I\u2019ve also been able to get to know other enthusiastic people who are motivated to make ASML an even better place to work.\u201c [->p<-] Being yourself at work includes feeling safe to express your uniqueness, particularly with regard to sexual orientation, gender identity and cultural expression. Employees in our BIPOC (black, indigenous and people of color) and LGBTQIA+ groups champion diversity that builds a strong and unique ASML DNA. [->p<-] The mission of our networks like\u00a0 [->p<-] and\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0is to ensure that ASML is a safe and great place to work, which explicitly welcomes diversity. As a member of one of these groups you\u2019ll be connected with like-minded people, participate in events, and learn from your colleagues through knowledge sharing and stories. [->p<-] \u201cI was inspired to get involved with the SHADES employee network because I see it as an active way to positively influence the BIPOC experience at ASML and beyond.\u201d [->p<-] Gender diversity is a concern in our industry. We recognize the need to recruit, retain and empower women and gender-diverse people at ASML. Women and WAVES are creating a strong, connected group of women and other colleagues, with the goal to see an increasing balance in leadership roles. We've been working hard toward that goal and we're already seeing some positive results, but we still have work to do. You can also join groups for parents, where you\u2019ll be able to connect with fellow ASML parents and find useful, practical information like nursing room locations and how to utilize parental leave policies. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] No matter who you are, you are welcome to join Women and WAVES to network, build your technical and soft skills through workshops, and be part of a team advocating to and cooperating with leadership. As part of the ASML team, you\u2019ll be able to join groups led by your colleagues that are striving to make ASML a more balanced company and a truly great place to work, meet, learn and share. [->p<-] \u201cBeing part of Women has been really beneficial to me in the sense of building connections with different people. It\u2019s taught me how to have an impact beyond my job description. It is amazing outlet for my passion for helping others and creating a gender-balanced and inclusive environment at ASML.\u201d [->p<-] Through the Parents network you'll be able to meet fellow ASML parents, support one another and share practical information, and promote family-friendly policies including: [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] People with a form of neurodiversity (for example, those on the autism spectrum) are highly valued at ASML, as we know the importance of analytical thinking, good logic, creativity and out-of-the-box thinking.\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0brings together the many people at ASML who are neurodiverse and provides a space to be understood and connect with others. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] This network hosts events like caf\u00e9 sessions, as well as talks that anyone in ASML can join to hear about the experiences of someone who is neurodiverse. And, as part of these groups, you can also become an ambassador \u2013 spreading the word about neurodiversity and being a champion for inclusivity at ASML. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Read our\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0about the Atypical network. [->p<-] \u201cIt might feel scary to be open about your neurodiversity but, in the end, doing so can open doors. Our network makes it easier for everyone to share their experience. I am also an ethics liaison, so anyone who is neurodiverse and feels they are not being treated fairly can come to us and we will support them. Our goal is an ASML where neurodiversity is embraced, so we will not be necessary anymore.\u201d [->p<-] Military veterans possess valuable experience and skills that are in high demand at ASML. Many veterans have found fulfilling post-service careers in tech at ASML. In the US, our Veterans employee network provides outreach to veterans and their families in the form of scholarships, professional development, military speaker series and networking opportunities. ASML partners with ACP (American Corporate Partners), a nonprofit organization that assists veterans in their transition from the armed services to the civilian workforce through free mentorships. Many of our ASML veterans have been paired as mentors with transitioning service members. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Read our\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0about veterans at ASML. [->p<-] \u201cConnecting veterans together has provided a sense of purpose; whether that be to work on a project, share stories or create development opportunities. In addition, it has given me a greater appreciation for the different veteran experiences and what we can learn from each other.\u201d [->p<-] Beside our formalized groups, we have a wide range of sport and hobby clubs that you can join. Soccer, basketball, sailing, motorbiking, running, music, board games, and cricket are just a few of our clubs, not to mention our famous robotic soccer team. [->p<-] Curious about what life at ASML is really like? You now can discover how we work, play and thrive, through an exclusive VR experience full of games and challenges.\u00a0\u00a0 [->p<-] Take a tour of our Veldhoven campus in the Netherlands and learn more about the employee services our teams enjoy, the sports we love to do, what we like to eat, and where we socialize with other colleagues.\u00a0\u00a0 [->p<-] Access the experience by simply clicking the link below or by scanning the QR code with your phone.\u00a0  [->p<-] Inspiration, education, entertainment \u2013 there\u2019s loads to discover at our ASML events [->p<-] We gather together at events to connect and collaborate \u2013 from an annual technology conference to a music festival featuring our very own talented employees. [->p<-] The meeting is an opportunity to connect, reflect and celebrate the past years\u2019 achievements.  [->p<-]  share key company developments and the strategy for the year ahead. In \u2018normal\u2019 times, thousands of ASML people attend the live event in Veldhoven, with colleagues gathering in locations around the world to follow the live web stream. [->p<-] In February 2021, nearly a year into the COVID-19 pandemic and working almost exclusively from home, we wanted to not only inform our colleagues but to reconnect and come together again. With that in mind, the virtual All Employee Meeting was created \u2013 complete with a DJ, a virtual reconstruction of the main plaza in our Veldhoven campus, polls and live questions from participants to the speakers. [->p<-] With tens of thousands of colleagues all over the world, our annual All Employee Meeting is a major event on the ASML calendar. [->p<-] Nowhere is the powerful impact of ASML\u2019s R&D more tangible than at our annual Technology Conference. What started out 22 years ago as a knowledge-sharing event among engineers has become one of the world\u2019s largest technology insights and innovation conferences. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] In 2020, the event went\u00a0 [->p<-]  for the first time and this year we got the best of both of worlds by combining online and in person events to connect nearly 10,000 ASML employees, thought leaders and key partners from all over the world. [->p<-] Regular Tech Talks give you the opportunity to hear guest speakers share the latest developments, insights and achievements on a wide variety of technology subjects. [->p<-] From the sustainability of energy sources to the societal implications of robotics, these talks spark new ideas and inspire employees to view their challenges from a different perspective. Watch this video to see one of our most recent talks. [->p<-] Have you got a musical talent? ASML on Stage is our yearly music festival starring talented ASML employees. [->p<-] Everyone can bring family and friends to enjoy the performances that cover music and dance of all genres and styles. In the Netherlands, ASML on Stage is hosted in the Muziekgebouw Eindhoven. ASML supports this venue and co-organizes events and programs that target diverse audiences. [->p<-] We\u2019re making bingo cool again, through a global online event for the whole family. [->p<-] With the global pandemic affecting all of us, fun has been in short supply over the past few months. To raise each other\u2019s spirits, we hosted the ASML Bingo Show for employees and their families. Participants from all over the world experienced music, fun and \u2013 of course \u2013 an exciting game of Bingo, with prizes including theme park tickets and gift packages. Watch this video of the event. [->p<-] For example, as part of our long-standing partnership with the\u00a0 [->p<-] , the virtual museum doors were opened for ASML employees worldwide to enjoy an exclusive tour. [->p<-] During this live event, colleagues explored the life and work of the world-famous painter from Brabant, the region where the headquarters of ASML is located. The museum\u2019s art historians walked us through the galleries, sharing the stories behind the masterpieces. ASML employees can re-watch this tour any time. [->p<-] The countdown to the Lunar New Year is a time for joy and celebration across our offices in Asia. Past celebrations have included performances, award ceremonies, lucky draws and banquets. [->p<-] In some countries within Asia, leaders of ASML gather annually to celebrate the past year and set priorities for the coming one. Attendees hear from country managers and connect with their fellow colleagues. [->p<-] These unmissable events, with different schedules each year, are a fun opportunity to get active together. Employees, with a mix of fun team and individual activities. [->p<-] In Taiwan, ASML hosts an annual picnic in the park for employees to relax and spend a day with their family and colleagues. [->p<-] Enjoy this annual immersive experience of light art and design. We organize tours for employees and their families, where you\u2019ll also see ASML\u2019s very own sponsored piece. [->p<-] If the season is just right, you can take part in the Dutch tradition of skating over the beautiful canals, ponds and lakes. Join our ice skating club to attend classes and outings. [->p<-] PSV soccer club hosts sports clinics where ASML people can learn from the best. [->p<-] We provide the flexibility and support, you put in the effort and passion [->p<-] We\u2019ve experienced unprecedented growth over the past five years. To put this in context, if you started with ASML in 2015 you would have had around 14,680 colleagues. These days, a new hire is one of more than 29,000 people working for ASML across the globe. [->p<-] To manage this growth and maintain our technological leadership, we need to ensure the right knowledge is available to our people at the right time. [->p<-] Developing our people is crucial to the sustained success of our business. In an innovative, high-tech, fast-changing industry like ours, it\u2019s vital to strengthen and continuously invest in you. [->p<-] We know that the complexity of our products means that new (and even existing) employees can face steep learning curves. [->p<-] This is why onboarding at ASML is so important. We dedicate significant effort to the onboarding process, including offering you interactive and engaging courses to kick-start your career with us. And you won\u2019t be alone. From your first day, you\u2019ll be connected to a \u2018buddy\u2019 \u2013 someone from your team who\u2019s familiar with ASML and able to help you find your way within the company. [->p<-] As your journey with ASML evolves, you\u2019ll never stop learning. We have our own technical development centers for employees from development & engineering,\u00a0 [->p<-]  and manufacturing departments. [->p<-] Driving your own development is easier said than done. It starts with clarity on what skill or behavior you would like to develop. [->p<-] This is followed by motivation to make a change, bolstered by feedback from the people close to you and structured with a concrete development plan that we support. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] The days of a linear career are behind us. That\u2019s why with ASML, rather than a career path, you\u2019ll have a career playground. We encourage you to gain experience across departments and regions, connect with colleagues with different expertise who you can share and learn with, and ultimately develop your own skills and passions. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] You\u2019ll also have the freedom to pursue any one of our more defined career tracks: you can specialize technically, become a manager, or grow into project management. Examples of ASML\u2019s employee development programs include\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0and\u00a0 [->p<-] . [->p<-] Development also includes having direction and aspirations. [->p<-] Once a year, we host a career festival for our employees. This festival connects current employees to other departments in ASML, showcasing the variety of opportunities open to you as an employee. It\u2019s also an opportunity to build your network within ASML, fostering connections beyond your direct team. [->p<-] \u201cI have worked in a range of exciting roles. From software developer, to architect, to project lead and group lead, and on products that include our DUV systems as well as our most advanced EUV systems. I get to play with robots and lasers and be challenged \u2013 all while growing my career!\u201d [->p<-] Most of our trainings take place on the job, given the nature of our innovative and collaborative business. We promote the 70-20-10 approach for your learning, meaning that 70% of your learning will be on the job, 20% through coaching, and 10% through training courses. [->p<-] We offer a broad range of learning interventions, ranging from classroom training to personal coaching, online assessments to business simulation games, and computer-based training to potential acceleration programs. Our employees learn through their preferred methods, either self-driven or classroom-based. After all, we believe you know best how you learn best. [->p<-] How you learn and develop at ASML is up to you, but it might include learning Lean and Agile working methodologies, participating in courses on conflict management or design thinking, or diving into change management. [->p<-] In some regions, you\u2019ll be able take advantage of what we call a \u2018Permanent employability day\u2019 \u2013 one day a year where you can work exclusively on your own personal development, whatever that means to you. On this non-work day, agreed on with your manager, you\u2019ll be freed up to work on your training, development or health. [->p<-] To strengthen your personal development, you can request support form a personal coach. [->p<-] Coaching is a social form of learning that is less structured and more self-directed than a traditional training-based approach. [->p<-] While many of our coaches are based in  [->p<-] , they are able to provide virtual coaching. We are also building up a global coaching pool for all the other regions. [->p<-] Our coach pool comprises both external and internal people, all who are certified and can guarantee your confidentiality. [->p<-] \u201cA few years ago, I felt like I was walking in circles because of perceived blockages and limitations. After talking to a coach, I was better able to recognize what made me happy and what didn\u2019t. I am now much more decisive, which allows me to grow again. I am very grateful to my coach and to ASML. I feel much more balanced now.\u201d [->p<-] We are all about teamwork. Teams that are high performing are better equipped to solve complex issues, make the right decisions and come up with top class solutions. [->p<-] That\u2019s why we offer a toolkit including team interventions, development journeys and diagnostic tools to help our teams self-assess, set goals, and identify areas to develop and improve. Having access to these tools will help you collaborate, appreciate your team and build a sense of belonging \u2013 where challenging and caring for each other is a way of life. [->p<-] To remain a market leader, we have to provide unified direction. This means we need strong and authentic leadership to give our people a clear picture of where ASML is heading. [->p<-] As a leader at ASML, you will have support to assess and develop your leadership abilities and to identify which areas may benefit from additional focus. You\u2019ll also have the opportunity to attend our Annual Global Leadership Conference, along with around 3,000 other leaders and people managers within ASML. [->p<-] We also offer leadership programs where we fast-track the careers of our most promising managers through our Potential Acceleration Program. These programs ensure our managers are aware of what\u2019s expected of them, and help them develop the skills and competencies they need to become better leaders. [->p<-] Our values (challenge, collaborate and care) have been translated into a set of common behaviors (dos and don\u2019ts) describing how we should act, underpinned by our Code of Conduct. The values and behavioral expectations are integrated into our annual performance management approach. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Our people are requested to set yearly goals aligning with our values from the perspectives of both their team and as an individual. Throughout the year, our employees and managers discuss conduct regularly and are encouraged to request feedback on their behavior from their colleagues and stakeholders (360 degree feedback). At the end of the year, our people are evaluated and structured appraisal questions about our values are included in a year-end feedback form.* [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] In each step, employees are directed to information about our culture and values content on our intranet via direct links in our Human Resources system supporting our performance management process. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] By integrating our values into our employee performance evaluations, we provide a consistent approach in addressing behavioral expectations and ensuring adherence to our Code of Conduct as part of our annual performance management cycle. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] At ASML we value high-performance individuals with a strong focus on well-being. Your health and work-life balance come first, and we support you in achieving your true potential and staying happy and thriving. [->p<-] Care is a core value at ASML and in terms of well-being it means we support you in leading a healthy, productive and balanced life. This way you can achieve your true potential and stay happy and thriving. After all, we can only succeed as an organization when everyone on the ASML team can give their best. [->p<-] Our well-being program and its ambassadors are focused on ensuring you have all the resources you need to thrive. You can attend a variety of well-being events focused around mental and physical health. [->p<-] Mental health encompasses our emotional, behavioral and psychological well-being \u2013 how we feel, act and think. It determines how we handle stress, make choices and contribute to our family and community. [->p<-] Physical health includes everything about the normal functioning of the body. It\u2019s about your nutrition, physical fitness, and sleep. Maintaining a healthy body allows us to get the most out of our daily activities without undue fatigue or physical stress. [->p<-] The social aspect relates to the relationships we form with other people, which are vital for our mental and emotional well-being. From socializing with colleagues to maintaining healthy personal relationships, it emphasizes our need to connect to others. At ASML, you\u2019ll find a\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0like\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0and Green, focused on bringing people together for a common cause. [->p<-] Financial health is important for an overall balanced life and directly contributes to your overall well-being. Money problems may impact mental health and add stress to your relationships. [->p<-] At ASML, we offer holistic support on well-being matters for all employees globally. This includes well-being training and masterclasses, on-campus events and online workshops. [->p<-] Our Veldhoven campus in the Netherlands has a dedicated well-being center. There you can enjoy the services of a physiotherapist and a psychologist by booking a physical or mental health check. In addition, you\u2019ll have access to a gym, a yoga room and a running track. We\u2019ve also set up an Employee Assistance Program that offers confidential support to everyone facing personal or professional challenges. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] We support you with your physical health by organizing group activities for our teams, free yoga classes and even endorsing marathon runs. We also support your nutrition education with free courses and offer healthy food choices on-campus. [->p<-] Our well-being portal, accessible by all employees globally, offers a variety of tools, both for individuals and teams, that target mindfulness, social intelligence, stress management and time management \u2013 among other things. Dedicated learning resources are available to support employees on their paths to sustainable well-being at work and in life. Employees can find and sign up for well-being events happening on campus and online, such as yoga classes, workshops and lectures on well-being. Certain regions also have access to a well-being app that offers meditation and mindfulness coaching. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] You can also connect with others through our\u00a0 [->p<-] . For example, in the Netherlands, you can join a 12-week well-being program with our friends at\u00a0 [->p<-] . [->p<-] Mental health is just as important as physical health. However, taking care of your mind isn\u2019t always as straightforward. Discover some of the simplest, most insightful tips from our company psychologist to help you navigate your own mental wellness at work, in life and beyond. [->p<-] A great working environment is key to well-being and productivity. At ASML, we offer resources and equipment to help you set up a healthy workspace from wherever you are working. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Our campuses around the world are inspiring places to work. In Europe, Asia and the US we have bright, open-plan offices, with good air quality and ergonomically designed workspaces. You\u2019ll also find secluded spaces to help you focus, meeting rooms to foster collaboration, and comfortable break rooms. [->p<-] Collaboration and innovation are in our DNA. We love to collaborate in person and connect with our colleagues, but we also want to maintain flexibility. Therefore, we offer a policy that allows you to combine working from the office with remote working. [->p<-] Check out this episode from our well-being series in collaboration with PSV, where the club\u2019s lifestyle coach Pablo Botermans shares his top well-being tips. [->p<-] What your compensation and benefits package could look like as an ASML employee [->p<-] Excellence recognizes excellence. We want to attract and retain you \u2013 the very best talent \u2013 and for you to share in the success you help build. As an ASML employee, you\u2019ll receive a highly competitive package. [->p<-] ASML pushes the limits of what\u2019s possible every day, and we need the best and brightest minds from around the world to do it. [->p<-] We want you to join ASML to be part of progress. And we want you to stay, because you feel your individual contribution is recognized and rewarded. [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] Therefore we provide an attractive compensation and benefits package such as a competitive salary, incentive plan, flexible working hours, remote working arrangements, part time working options, maternity, paternity and other care leave. [->p<-] We aim for global consistency in our remuneration policies, but naturally we also respect common practices and benchmark ourselves in the local markets where our employees are based. [->p<-] You\u2019ll see this reflected in variations of our compensation and benefits packages from country to country (detailed below). We annually assess gender pay parity, to ensure that we continue to provide fair and equitable salaries. [->p<-] You will receive a competitive and comprehensive total reward package when you join ASML in the US. This includes generous health and welfare benefits, performance-based variable pay plans, long-term incentive plans for outstanding performance, and personal development opportunities to encourage career growth.\u00a0 [->p<-] *Differences based on salary grade may apply [->p<-] \u201cFor me, \u2018vacation days\u2019 really mean \u2018family\u2019. As I\u2019m living abroad, this amount of vacation days means that \u2013 in normal times \u2013 I\u2019m able to visit my parents regularly. It\u2019s a comfort to know that I can be with them whenever they need me.\u201d [->p<-] If you are an 'international local hire' \u2013 in other words, you were hired to work in a different country or state than where you currently live \u2013 ASML will support the relocation of you and your direct family members (spouse and children). [->p<-] We\u2019ll provide support for immigration, travel, shipping personal belongings, cultural awareness and language training, and tax advice. And, of course, you and your family will have support from us as you settle in. [->p<-] If you\u2019re in the Netherlands but living far from Veldhoven, we may be able to provide financial assistance to help you move closer to the action."]], ["div", ["[->div<-] We saved your job [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] We have identified four well-being dimensions, including physical, mental, social and financial. Discover more about the four dimensions of a balanced life and how we support you in safeguarding or promoting each of them according to your needs. [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n [->div<-] \n"]], ["tr", ["[->tr<-] "]], ["td", ["[->td<-] "]], ["th", ["[->th<-] "]], ["font", ["[->font<-] "]], ["li", ["[->li<-] Locations of ASML\u2019s breastfeeding/lactation facilities [->li<-] ASML\u2019s arrangements with local childcare facilities [->li<-] Competitive salary [->li<-] 13th month payment [->li<-] 8% holiday allowance [->li<-] 40 days paid leave: 27 vacation days and 13 ADV days (reduction of working hours) [->li<-] Variable pay [->li<-] Pension plan [->li<-] Collective health insurance plan [->li<-] Employee share purchase plan [->li<-] Commuting allowance [->li<-] Reimbursement for relocation expenses [->li<-] Training and development opportunities, including educational assistance through our Global Training and Studies program [->li<-] Competitive salary [->li<-] Paid vacation and other time off [->li<-] Performance-based variable pay plan [->li<-] Long-term incentive plan for outstanding performance [->li<-] Comprehensive health and welfare benefits package [->li<-] Life insurance and retirement savings plan [->li<-] Employee share purchase plan [->li<-] Employee referral bonus [->li<-] Long-time service award [->li<-] Training and development opportunities, including educational assistance through our Global Training and Studies program"]], ["small", ["[->small<-] "]], ["strong", ["[->strong<-] Ready to be part of progress? [->strong<-] Green [->strong<-] Next\u00a0 [->strong<-] Seniors\u00a0 [->strong<-] Proud\u00a0 [->strong<-] SHADES [->strong<-] Atypical [->strong<-] If you don\u2019t discover a group based on your interests, you can always create your own. With thousands of colleagues in your local area and around the world, it's easy to connect with people who have the same interests as you and colleagues outside of your department while having fun doing something you love. [->strong<-] Ready to be part of progress? [->strong<-] Ready to be part of progress? [->strong<-] Ready to be part of progress? [->strong<-] Our well-being offerings [->strong<-] Ready to be part of progress? [->strong<-] Ready to be part of progress?"]], ["h1", ["[->h1<-] What\u2019s life like at ASML?"]], ["h2", ["[->h2<-] Search [->h2<-] Supporting you to make a difference [->h2<-] Supporting technology education [->h2<-] Find your people [->h2<-] Making connections through our communities [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Bringing bright minds together [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Drive your development [->h2<-] Coaching [->h2<-] Well-being at ASML \u2013 Healthy, happy and thriving [->h2<-] Enable third party cookies to play this video [->h2<-] Sharing success, recognizing excellence [->h2<-] Learn [->h2<-] Work At ASML [->h2<-] Invest [->h2<-] Get in touch"]], ["h3", ["[->h3<-] Life at ASML [->h3<-] PURPOSE [->h3<-] Networks & Clubs [->h3<-] Hop on a virtual reality tour of our Veldhoven campus! [->h3<-] Events [->h3<-] LEARN & DEVELOP [->h3<-] Well-being [->h3<-] Benefits"]], ["h4", ["[->h4<-] Volunteering [->h4<-] Promoting sports, arts and music initiatives to boost community culture [->h4<-] Local outreach [->h4<-] Matching Gifts program [->h4<-] Support for startups [->h4<-] Lenette, business process analyst and board member of Seniors [->h4<-] Sander, Next community member [->h4<-] Charnay, senior people services leader and SHADES chair [->h4<-] All Employee Meeting [->h4<-] Technology Conference [->h4<-] Tech Talks [->h4<-] ASML on Stage [->h4<-] The ASML Bingo Show [->h4<-] Van Gogh virtual tour [->h4<-] Local events in Asia [->h4<-] There are endless opportunities to learn at ASML. We\u2019ll help you identify what you want to achieve, while giving you the freedom to be in the driver\u2019s seat of your development and personal growth. [->h4<-] Invested in you [->h4<-] Getting up to speed [->h4<-] Steer your own career [->h4<-] Internal career festival [->h4<-] Blended learning [->h4<-] Team development [->h4<-] Leadership development [->h4<-] Code of Conduct in our employee performance management system [->h4<-] Your well-being at ASML [->h4<-] Well-being pillars [->h4<-] Work well, live well [->h4<-] A positive work environment [->h4<-] Hybrid working [->h4<-] What\u2019s behind the benefits [->h4<-] Find out what your compensation and benefits could be in the different countries where ASML works. [->h4<-] Meet Burcu, scrum master in the Netherlands [->h4<-] Relocation support [->h4<-] Social Media"]], ["h5", ["[->h5<-] Meet Suze, manufacturing engineering team lead and volunteer tutor [->h5<-] Meet Maria, project lead with ASML\u2019s Van Gogh research project [->h5<-] Meet Patrick, senior research director and startup supporter [->h5<-] If you are sustainability conscious [->h5<-] Camille, Nick and Tom, Green board members [->h5<-] If you want to connect with people in different career phases [->h5<-] If you\u2019re an advocate for diversity and inclusion [->h5<-] If you want to be inspired by women at ASML [->h5<-] Annelieze, system qualification group lead and board member of Women [->h5<-] If you want to connect with other parents [->h5<-] If you\u2019d like to be part of our neurodiversity network [->h5<-] Arnout, supplier audit support and Atypical board member [->h5<-] If you\u2019re a veteran looking for camaraderie and support [->h5<-] Christopher Lopez, senior Customer Support portfolio manager and Veterans chair [->h5<-] Sports and hobbies [->h5<-] Meet Hans Liu, group lead [->h5<-] Ron, mechanic and coachee [->h5<-] Mental well-being [->h5<-] Physical well-being [->h5<-] Social well-being [->h5<-] Financial well-being [->h5<-] Want to preview the well-being resources you\u2019ll have access to with ASML? [->h5<-] Fair and balanced remuneration [->h5<-] ASML compensation and benefits in\u00a0 [->h5<-] * [->h5<-] ASML compensation and benefits in\u00a0 [->h5<-] * [->h5<-] ASML compensation and benefits in Asia*"]], ["h6", ["[->h6<-] "]], ["span", ["[->span<-] Scroll [->span<-] You can make a positive social impact at ASML. We know that being part of a community means caring not only for our employees but also for the people we\u2019re connected to outside our organization. [->span<-] We live in an increasingly digital society. Through local activities, our aim is to help people of all ages and backgrounds to develop their skills, shape the digital future and to take full advantage of its potential. [->span<-] We amplify the impact of our employees\u2019 charitable actions by supporting the causes they feel passionate about. Our Matching Gifts program gives employees a voice in the distribution of ASML's financial contributions to qualified organizations. [->span<-] \u201cThey (young entrepreneurs) often like to chat with me \u2013 their calls are for example, \u2018what IP do we have to protect\u2019. There are also very real technical challenges \u2013 preferences between scanning with a neutron beam or something else. They see ASML as having experience in almost everything, so they are looking for one contact person to be able to call and ask for advice.\u201d [->span<-] Click for more details [->span<-] Besides being a great way to socialize with colleagues, getting involved with a group can help build your professional network while doing something you are passionate about. [->span<-] More about diversity and inclusion [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Unlock our world [->span<-] Click for more details [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Many of our events involve partners of ASML. [->span<-] Image by: Jan Kees Steenman [->span<-] New Year and year-end celebrations [->span<-] Leadership meeting [->span<-] Sports and family days [->span<-] Festival in the Park [->span<-] Local events in the Netherlands [->span<-] GLOW Eindhoven art festival [->span<-] Ice skating [->span<-] PSV clinics [->span<-] Click for more details [->span<-] Click for more details [->span<-] Read the story [->span<-] Disabled [->span<-] Enabled [->span<-] Click for more details [->span<-] Click for more details [->span<-] Close [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] / [->span<-] Manage cookie settings [->span<-] Copyright \u00a9 2019-2026 (ASML) All Rights Reserved"]], ["b", ["[->b<-] "]], ["em", ["[->em<-] * Examples of questions included in our feedback form about behavioral expectations aligning with our values: [->em<-] \u00a0 [->em<-] How did you demonstrate behaviors that align with our values (challenge, collaborate and care)? How could you have better demonstrated behaviors aligning with our values? Provide examples. [->em<-] \u00a0 [->em<-] For people managers: How did you demonstrate behaviors that align with ASML\u2019s leadership standards (role model, coach, people leader and business leader)? How could you have better demonstrated behaviors aligning with these standards? Provide examples. [->em<-] Benefits/perks may vary depending on the nature of your employment with ASML and the country where you work."]]]], "title": ["ASML | The world's supplier to the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "ASML | The world's supplier to the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "Saved jobs | ASML ASML Logo", "About the company | ASML - Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "About ASML | Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "ASML at a glance | Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "ASML vision & mission | Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "Company organization | ASML - Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "Our history | ASML - Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "Locations | ASML - Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "Corporate governance | ASML - Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "Board of Management | ASML - Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "Supervisory Board | ASML - Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "ASML shareholders | Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "Code of Conduct | ASML - Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "How we manage risk | ASML - Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "Auditors | ASML - Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "Downloads - Corporate governance | ASML - Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "ASML sustainability | Supplying the semiconductor industry ASML Logo", "Community engagement | ASML ASML Logo", "Education - Community engagement | ASML ASML Logo", "Sports, arts and music - Community engagement 